@ \chapter{Boot sequence}

Drol uses a custom Broderbund boot chain, not DOS 3.3. The disk is not
DOS-formatted and has no catalog. The entire boot sequence is:

\begin{enumerate}
\item The Disk II controller PROM (P5A) reads Track 0, Sector 0 to [[$0800]]
   and jumps to [[$0801]]. This is the standard Apple II boot process (``boot0'').
\item Boot1 at [[$0801]] loads 10 more sectors from Track 0 to [[$5000--$59FF]]
   using the PROM's re-entry point at [[$Cn5C]].
\item Boot1 copies the Apple II ROM to language card RAM, relocates the
   loader and RWTS code, and jumps to the loader.
\item The loader reads the game data from subsequent tracks into memory
   and launches the game.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Disk layout}

The P5A PROM reads sectors in the order they physically appear on the disk
as it rotates. Due to the 16-sector format's physical interleave, the
sectors pass under the head in this order:

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{cccccccccccccccc}
0 & 7 & E & 6 & D & 5 & C & 4 & B & 3 & A & 2 & 9 & 1 & 8 & F \\
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The [[.dsk]] file format stores sectors by sector number (0--F).
To find the file offset of the Nth sector read by the PROM:

\begin{verbatim}
    POSITION_ORDER = [0, 7, E, 6, D, 5, C, 4, B, 3, A, 2, 9, 1, 8, F]
    sector_number  = POSITION_ORDER[N]
    file_offset    = track * 4096 + sector_number * 256
\end{verbatim}

\section{Track 0 memory map}

Boot0 reads Sector 0 to [[$0800]] (boot1 code). Boot1 then reads the next
10 sectors to [[$5000--$59FF]]:

\begin{center}
\ra{1.3}
\begin{tabular}{cccl}
\toprule
\thead{Position} & \thead{Sector} & \thead{Memory} & \thead{Contents} \\
\midrule
0 & 0 & [[$0800]] & Boot1 \\
1 & 7 & [[$5000]] & RWTS: sector read entry, address field reader, data field reader \\
2 & E & [[$5100]] & Loader subroutines: drive select, delay, seek, read track, init \\
3 & 6 & [[$5200]] & Seek routine continued, nibble constants \\
4 & D & [[$5300]] & Read buffer (zeros at boot, filled during sector reads) \\
5 & 5 & [[$5400]] & Page destination table (maps sectors to memory pages) \\
6 & C & [[$5500]] & Main loader dispatch \\
7 & 4 & [[$5600]] & Unused (all zeros) \\
8 & B & [[$5700]] & Zero page save area (initialized with boot-time ZP snapshot) \\
9 & 3 & [[$5800]] & RWTS high-level code (relocated to [[$BE00]]) \\
10 & A & [[$5900]] & Reset handlers and screen address table (relocated to [[$BF00]]) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

After loading, boot1 performs these relocations:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[$D000]]--[[$FFFF]]: Apple II ROM copied to language card RAM.
\item [[$D000]]--[[$D7FF]]: Copy of [[RWTS_ENTRY]]--[[$57FF]] (loader/RWTS under language card).
\item [[$BE00]]--[[$BEFF]]: Copy of [[RWTS_HIGH]]--[[$58FF]] (RWTS high-level code).
\item [[$BF00]]--[[$BFFF]]: Copy of [[RESET_HANDLERS]]--[[$59FF]] (reset handlers, screen address table).
\end{itemize}

The loader code thus lives in two places: at [[RWTS_ENTRY]]--[[$57FF]] in main RAM (where
it executes during loading), and at [[$D000]]--[[$D7FF]] under the language card (a
backup copy).

\section{Boot1}

Boot1 occupies Track 0, Sector 0 ([[$0800]]--[[$08BF]]). The first byte ([[$0800]])
is the sector count for boot0; the PROM reads this value and loads that many
sectors. Here it is [[$01]], meaning boot0 loads only Sector 0 itself. After
loading, boot0 sets [[DEST_PAGE]] = [[$09]] (the next destination page) and jumps to
[[$0801]].

@ Boot1 is the first code executed after the PROM's boot0. It operates in
three phases, re-entered at [[$0801]] by the PROM after each sector read:

\textbf{Phase 1} --- When [[DEST_PAGE]] = [[$09]] (immediately, since boot0 just set it):
switch to hi-res graphics mode, derive the slot number, patch the JMP
instruction for PROM re-entry, set reset vectors, and redirect
loading to [[$5000]] by setting [[$27]] = [[$50]].

\textbf{Phase 2} --- While [[DEST_PAGE]] $<$ [[$5A]]: jump to [[$Cn5C]] to read the next
sector. The PROM stores it at page [[DEST_PAGE]], increments [[DEST_PAGE]], and re-enters
[[$0801]]. This loads 10 sectors to [[RWTS_ENTRY]]--[[$59FF]].

\textbf{Phase 3} --- When [[DEST_PAGE]] $\ge$ [[$5A]]: all sectors loaded. Copy ROM to
language card, relocate loader and RWTS, display splash text, and jump
to the loader entry at [[LOADER_INIT]].

<<boot1 defines>>=

; Zero page locations used by boot1 and the PROM.
DEST_PAGE       = $27           ; PROM: destination page for next sector read
SLOT_X16        = $2B           ; Slot number * 16 (e.g. $60 for slot 6)

; Soft switches for graphics mode.
SW_HIRES        = $C057         ; Hi-res mode
SW_PAGE1        = $C054         ; Display page 1
SW_FULLSCR      = $C052         ; Full screen (no text window)
SW_GRAPHICS     = $C050         ; Graphics mode (vs text)

; Language card soft switches.
LC_BANK1_RWROM  = $C081         ; LC bank 1: write RAM, read ROM
LC_BANK1_ROROM  = $C080         ; LC bank 1: read-only ROM (write-protect RAM)

; Reset and NMI vectors.
SOFTEV          = $03F2         ; Soft entry vector (reset handler)
SOFTEV_CHK      = $03F4         ; Checksum for SOFTEV ($03F3 EOR #$A5)
NMIVEC          = $FFFC         ; NMI vector (2 bytes, in language card)

; Monitor ROM routines.
MON_HOME        = $FC58         ; Clear screen

; Loader variables in RESET_R page.
LDR_TRACK       = $BF48         ; Current track number
LDR_SLOT        = $BF49         ; Slot number * 16
LDR_PHASE       = $BF4A         ; Boot phase counter ($FF = first boot)

; Loader entry point (in loader binary, not accessible by label).
LOADER_INIT     = $51C0         ; Loader init entry point

; Text screen.
TEXT_SCREEN      = $0400         ; First line of text screen
@

<<boot1 entry>>=

        ORG $0800
        SUBROUTINE

        ; Boot sector entry -- multi-phase loader for Drol.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   DEST_PAGE -- destination page set by boot0 PROM
        ;   X -- slot number * 16 (from PROM)
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Phase 1 (DEST_PAGE <- #$09): switches to hi-res graphics, patches
        ;     re-entry JMP and reset vector, redirects loading to RWTS_ENTRY.
        ;   Phase 2 (DEST_PAGE<$5A): returns to PROM to read next sector.
        ;   Phase 3 (DEST_PAGE>=$5A): copies ROM to language card, relocates
        ;     RWTS to RWTS_RELOAD, backs up loader to $D000, decodes splash text,
        ;     and jumps to loader entry.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   SOFTEV, SOFTEV_CHK, NMIVEC, LDR_SLOT, LDR_PHASE, LDR_TRACK,
        ;   RWTS_RELOAD-$BFFF (RWTS), $D000-$D7FF (loader backup), language card RAM

BOOT1_SECTORS:
        .BYTE $01               ; Sector count for boot0 (just this sector)

; --- Entry point: PROM jumps here after each sector read ---

BOOT1_ENTRY:
        LDA DEST_PAGE           ; Current destination page
        CMP #$09                ; First entry? (boot0 sets DEST_PAGE <- #$09)
        BNE .check_done         ; No, check if loading is complete

; --- Phase 1: first entry after boot0 ---

        BIT SW_HIRES            ; Switch to hi-res graphics mode
        BIT SW_PAGE1            ; Display page 1
        BIT SW_FULLSCR          ; Full screen (no text window)
        BIT SW_GRAPHICS         ; Graphics (not text)

        TXA                     ; X = slot * 16 (from PROM)
        LSR                     ; Shift right 4 times
        LSR                     ;   to get slot number
        LSR                     ;
        LSR                     ;
        ORA #$C0                ; Form $Cn (slot ROM page)
        STA .jmp_reentry+2      ; Patch JMP target high byte
        STA SOFTEV+1            ; Reset vector high byte = $Cn
        EOR #$A5                ; Compute checksum
        STA SOFTEV_CHK          ; Store reset vector checksum
        LDA #$00
        STA SOFTEV              ; Reset vector low byte = $00
        LDA #$5C
        STA .jmp_reentry+1      ; JMP low byte = $5C (PROM re-entry)
        LDA #$50
        STA DEST_PAGE           ; Redirect loading to RWTS_ENTRY

; --- Phase 2: continue loading, or Phase 3: done ---

.check_done:
        LDA DEST_PAGE
        CMP #$5A                ; Loaded all 10 sectors? ($5000-$59FF)
        BCS .loading_done       ; Yes, proceed to phase 3
.jmp_reentry:
        JMP $C65C               ; No, read next sector (patched to $Cn5C)

; --- Phase 3: all sectors loaded ---

.loading_done:

; Copy the entire Apple II ROM ($D000-$FFFF) to language card RAM.
; Reading $C081 twice selects LC bank 1 for writing with ROM readable.
; The LDA/STA through the same pointer reads from ROM, writes to RAM.

        LDA LC_BANK1_RWROM      ; LC bank 1: write RAM, read ROM
        LDA LC_BANK1_RWROM      ; (must read twice to enable writes)

        LDX #$30                ; $30 pages = $D000-$FFFF (48 pages)
        LDY #$00
        STY $00                 ; Pointer low = $00
        LDA #$D0
        STA $01                 ; Pointer high = $D0
.copy_rom:
        LDA ($00),Y             ; Read from ROM
        STA ($00),Y             ; Write to LC RAM
        INY
        BNE .copy_rom
        INC $01                 ; Next page
        DEX
        BNE .copy_rom

; Set NMI vector in language card to point to RESET_R (reset handler).

        LDA #$BF
        STA NMIVEC+1            ; NMI vector high = $BF
        STA SOFTEV+1            ; Reset vector high = $BF
        EOR #$A5
        STA SOFTEV_CHK          ; Reset checksum
        LDA #$00
        STA NMIVEC              ; NMI vector low = $00
        STA SOFTEV              ; Reset vector low = $00

; Copy $5800-$59FF to RWTS_RELOAD-$BFFF (RWTS and reset handlers).

        LDX #$00
.copy_rwts:
        LDA $5800,X
        STA $BE00,X
        LDA $5900,X
        STA $BF00,X
        INX
        BNE .copy_rwts

; Store slot number and initialize loader state.

        LDX SLOT_X16            ; Slot * 16 from PROM
        STX LDR_SLOT            ; Save for loader
        LDA #$FF
        STA LDR_PHASE           ; Phase = $FF (first boot, not yet started)
        LDA #$00
        STA LDR_TRACK           ; Current track = 0

; Copy $5000-$57FF to $D000-$D7FF (loader backup under language card).
; This is a self-modifying loop: the source and destination addresses
; are incremented in-place.

        LDX #$00
.copy_loader:
        LDA $5000,X             ; Source: $5000 (patched)
        STA $D000,X             ; Dest: $D000 (patched)
        INX
        BNE .copy_loader
        INC .copy_loader+2      ; Increment source page
        INC .copy_loader+5      ; Increment dest page
        LDA .copy_loader+2      ; Check source page
        CMP #$58                ; Done when source reaches $5800
        BNE .copy_loader

; Switch back to ROM (write-protect language card).

        LDA LC_BANK1_ROROM

; Clear the text screen.

        JSR MON_HOME

; XOR-decode 40 bytes from SPLASH_TEXT to the text screen.
; In this disk image the source bytes are all zero, so $0400 gets
; filled with $AB (the XOR key), which displays as "+" characters.
; On the original disk this may have been a Broderbund copyright line.

        LDX #$00
.decode_text:
        LDA SPLASH_TEXT,X
        EOR #$AB
        STA TEXT_SCREEN,X       ; First line of text screen
        INX
        CPX #$28                ; 40 columns
        BNE .decode_text

; Enter the loader.

        JMP LOADER_INIT         ; Loader init entry point

; Pad to fill the rest of the sector with zeros.
; SPLASH_TEXT-$08F7: splash text (XOR-encoded, all zeros in this image).

        DS $D0-(*-$0800),0

SPLASH_TEXT:
        DS $28,0                ; 40 bytes of encoded text (all $00)

        DS $0900-*,0            ; Pad to end of sector
@ %def BOOT1_SECTORS BOOT1_ENTRY SPLASH_TEXT

<<boot1.asm>>=
        PROCESSOR 6502
<<boot1 defines>>
<<boot1 entry>>
@

\section{Loader}

After boot1 jumps to [[$51C0]], the loader takes over. The loader occupies
[[$5000--$59FF]] (loaded from Track 0 by boot1) and manages reading game
data from subsequent tracks into memory.

The loader has two entry points:
\begin{itemize}
\item [[$5000]]: Re-entry from game code. Saves zero page to [[$5700]],
  then falls through to [[$51C0]].
\item [[$51C0]]: Entry from boot1. Restores the slot and track numbers from
  [[$BF49]]/[[$BF48]] to zero page, then jumps to the main dispatch
  at [[$5500]].
\end{itemize}

The RWTS (Read/Write Track/Sector) uses standard Apple II 16-sector nibble
encoding with D5~AA~96 (address field) and D5~AA~AD (data field) prologues.
The 6-and-2 nibble translate table lives at [[$52D6--$53D5]], spanning the
RWTS work buffers at [[$5200]] and [[$5300]].

The [[RWTS_HIGH]]--[[$59FF]] region is relocated by boot1 to [[RWTS_RELOAD]]--[[$BFFF]] and contains
the high-level RWTS entry, reset handlers, screen buffer routines, and the
hi-res address lookup table. The loader itself never calls into the relocated
RWTS code; it uses its own sector reading routines at [[$5003]]--[[$50C6]]. The
relocated code at [[RWTS_RELOAD]]--[[$BFFF]] is used only by the game.

\subsection{Disk layout}

The 35-track disk is organized as follows:

\begin{center}
\ra{1.3}
\begin{tabular}{cl}
\toprule
\thead{Tracks} & \thead{Contents} \\
\midrule
0      & Boot1 + loader/RWTS ([[RWTS_ENTRY]]--[[$59FF]]) \\
1--4   & Persistent game code (loaded once at first boot) \\
5--9   & Level data set 0 (phase 0) \\
10--14 & Level data set 1 (phase 1) \\
15--19 & Level data set 2 (phase 2) \\
20--24 & Level data set 3 (phase 3) \\
25--34 & Unused \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\subsection{Memory map after first boot}

Memory is split into two categories: \textbf{persistent game code} loaded
once from tracks 1--4, and \textbf{swappable level data} loaded from a
5-track group that changes with each phase.

\begin{center}
\ra{1.3}
\begin{tabular}{lll}
\toprule
\thead{Address} & \thead{Source} & \thead{Type} \\
\midrule
[[$0100]]--[[$01EF]] & Track 1 S0--S1 $\to$ [[STAGE_STACK]], copied & Stack page init \\
[[$0200]]          & Track 5+ S0                          & Level data (swappable) \\
[[$0300]]--[[$03EF]] & Track 1 S0--S1 $\to$ [[STAGE_VECTORS]], copied & Vectors / data \\
[[$0400]]--[[$12FF]] & Tracks 1--2                           & Game code (persistent) \\
[[$1300]]--[[$18FF]] & Track 5+ S1--S6                       & Level data (swappable) \\
[[$1900]]--[[$1FFF]] & Track 2                               & Game code (persistent) \\
[[$2000]]--[[$3FFF]] & ---                                   & Hi-res page 1 (framebuffer, not loaded) \\
[[GAME_INIT_NOP]]--[[$47FF]] & Tracks 2--3                           & Game code (persistent, entry at [[GAME_INIT_NOP]]) \\
[[RWTS_ENTRY]]--[[$59FF]] & Track 0                               & Loader / RWTS (persistent) \\
[[STAGE_STACK]]--[[$5DFF]] & Track 1 S0--S1                        & Staging buffers \\
[[$5E00]]--[[$5FFF]] & Track 4 S10--S11                      & Game code (persistent) \\
[[$6000]]--[[$66FF]] & Track 3                               & Game code (persistent) \\
[[$6700]]--[[$72FF]] & Track 5+ S7--S15, Track 6+ S0--S2    & Level data (swappable) \\
[[$7300]]--[[$74FF]] & Track 3                               & Game code (persistent) \\
[[$7500]]--[[$7AFF]] & Track 6+ S3--S8                       & Level data (swappable) \\
[[$7B00]]--[[$8BFF]] & Tracks 3--4                           & Game code (persistent) \\
[[$8C00]]--[[$BDFF]] & Tracks 6+--9+                         & Level data (swappable) \\
[[RWTS_RELOAD]]--[[$BFFF]] & Track 0 ([[RWTS_HIGH]]--[[$59FF]]), relocated   & RWTS / reset handlers \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The game calls back to the loader via [[JMP $5000]] to swap in a new
level set. The loader cycles through phases 0--3, each reading 5
consecutive tracks (5--9, 10--14, 15--19, 20--24). Each phase replaces
75 pages (19,200 bytes) of level data while leaving the persistent
game code untouched.

<<loader defines>>=

; =========================================================================
;  Zero page locations
; =========================================================================

ZP_PTR          = $00          ; General pointer (2 bytes)
ZP_DEST         = $04          ; Sector data destination (2 bytes)
ZP_TEMP_A       = $0B          ; Temporary (seek: saved half-track)
ZP_TEMP_B       = $0C          ; Temporary (seek: accel index / addr checksum)
ZP_CUR_HTRK     = $0D          ; Current half-track (seek) / current sector
ZP_TGT_HTRK     = $0E          ; Target half-track (seek)
ZP_TGT_TRACK    = $0F          ; Target track for read
ZP_TBL_INDEX    = $10          ; Page table index
ZP_SLOT_X16     = $2B          ; Slot * 16
ZP_ADDR_VOL     = $2C          ; Address field: volume
ZP_ADDR_TRK     = $2D          ; Address field: track (also sector index)
ZP_ADDR_SEC     = $2E          ; Address field: sector
ZP_ADDR_CHK     = $2F          ; Address field: checksum
ZP_JOY_FLAG     = $44          ; Bit 7: joystick present
ZP_INPUT_1      = $52          ; Input handler pointer 1 (2 bytes)
ZP_INPUT_2      = $54          ; Input handler pointer 2 (2 bytes)
ZP_SEC_REMAIN   = $A0          ; Sectors remaining count
ZP_NREAD_TEMP   = $A0          ; Nibble read temp (shared)

; Sector buffer table: $90-$9F maps sector N to destination page.
; Entry is 0 if sector already read or not needed.
ZP_SEC_TABLE    = $90

; =========================================================================
;  Absolute addresses
; =========================================================================

GAME_INIT       = $4000         ; Game initialization entry point

; Loader persistent variables (in $BF page, survive ZP save/restore).
LDR_TRACK       = $BF48         ; Current track number
LDR_SLOT        = $BF49         ; Slot * 16
LDR_PHASE       = $BF4A         ; Boot phase counter ($FF = first boot)

; RWTS relocated addresses (code runs after boot1 relocates).
RWTS_RELOAD_SRC = $BE1E         ; Self-mod: source page for reload loop
RWTS_RELOAD_DST = $BE21         ; Self-mod: dest page for reload loop
RWTS_CONT       = $BEA3         ; Continue after RWTS reload
RWTS_RESET_LC   = $BEE0         ; Reset: copy ROM to language card
RWTS_SCROLL_UP  = $BF50         ; Scroll screen up routine
RWTS_SCROLL_DN  = $BF7F         ; Scroll screen down routine
RWTS_ADDR_TBL   = $BFC0         ; Hi-res screen address lookup table

; Disk I/O soft switches (offset by slot).
DISK_DATA       = $C08C         ; Read data latch
DISK_PHASE0_OFF = $C080         ; Stepper motor phase 0 off
DISK_MOTOR_OFF  = $C088         ; Drive motor off
DISK_MOTOR_ON   = $C089         ; Drive motor on

; Other hardware.
SW_PADDLE_TRIG  = $C070         ; Trigger paddle timer reset
SW_PADDLE_BTN0  = $C064         ; Paddle analog 0
SW_PADDLE_BTN1  = $C065         ; Paddle analog 1
SW_PUSH_BTN0    = $C061         ; Push button 0 (bit 7 = pressed)
SW_PUSH_BTN1    = $C062         ; Push button 1 (bit 7 = pressed)

; Monitor/ROM.
MON_INIT        = $FB2F         ; Initialize monitor
MON_HOME        = $FC58         ; Clear screen
MON_NORMAL      = $FE84         ; Normal text output mode
ROM_MACHID      = $FBB4         ; Machine identification byte

; Staging buffers (loaded from track 1, copied to STACK_PAGE/VECTOR_PAGE).
; STAGE_STACK ($5C00) and STAGE_VECTORS ($5D00) are real labels in
; drol.asm; these EQUs let loader.asm reference them (the two files
; assemble independently).
STAGE_STACK     = $5C00         ; Staging buffer for stack page
STAGE_VECTORS   = $5D00         ; Staging buffer for vector page
STACK_PAGE      = $0100         ; Stack page destination
VECTOR_PAGE     = $0300         ; Vector page destination

; Floor Y-coordinate table (indexed by floor number 1-4).
; Entry 0 is a $00 sentinel. Written by FIRST_BOOT.
FLOOR_Y_TABLE   = $03F8         ; Floor Y positions: $00,$43,$6B,$93,$BB

; Dummy pointer target for keyboard mode: any RAM address with bit 7 clear.
KBD_DUMMY_ADDR  = $6219         ; RAM byte always has bit 7 clear

; Game-code patch operands.  Loader writes one-time patches into three
; self-modifying immediate/operand bytes after disk load.  Each label is
; defined symbolically at its site in the game code; these EQUs let
; loader.asm reference them (the two files assemble independently):
;   SMC_ATTRACT_EXIT_JMP  -- JMP operand in START_ATTRACT; redirects the
;                            cold-boot exit from ATTRACT_LOOP to
;                            LIFE_LOST_HANDLER (shared extras-animation
;                            path).  Patched on every boot regardless of
;                            machine type.
;   SMC_KEY_RIGHT         -- CMP #imm at INPUT_DISPATCH's right-arrow
;                            check; patched to KEY_IIC_RIGHT on Apple IIc.
;   SMC_KEY_LEFT          -- CMP #imm at INPUT_DISPATCH's left-arrow
;                            check; patched to KEY_IIC_LEFT on IIc.
SMC_ATTRACT_EXIT_JMP = $72BA    ; JMP operand low-byte in START_ATTRACT
SMC_KEY_RIGHT   = $600E         ; CMP #imm operand in INPUT_DISPATCH
SMC_KEY_LEFT    = $6022         ; CMP #imm operand in INPUT_DISPATCH
LIFE_LOST_HANDLER = $7208       ; Exit target for patched START_ATTRACT

; Machine ID constants (from ROM_MACHID at $FBB4).
MACHID_IIC      = $08           ; Apple IIc marker byte

; Apple IIc arrow-key codes (different from II/IIe $88/$95).
KEY_IIC_LEFT    = $CB           ; IIc left-arrow: 'K' with high bit set
KEY_IIC_RIGHT   = $CC           ; IIc right-arrow: 'L' with high bit set

; Game entry.
ZP_GAME_ENTRY   = $4E           ; Indirect jump vector for game entry ($4E/$4F)
@

<<rwts entry>>=

        ORG $5000

; Entry point from game: save zero page then enter loader.
RWTS_ENTRY:
        JMP SAVE_ZP

; -------------------------------------------------------------------------
;  READ_ADDR_FIELD
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------

READ_ADDR_FIELD:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Read and verify a 16-sector address field.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_SLOT_X16 -- slot * 16 for disk I/O
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Scans for D5 AA 96 prologue, reads 4 odd-even encoded
        ;   bytes (volume, track, sector, checksum), verifies the
        ;   running XOR checksum is zero, and checks for the DE
        ;   epilogue byte.
        ;
        ; Outputs:
        ;   Carry clear = success, carry set = error
        ;   ZP_ADDR_VOL/TRK/SEC/CHK ($2C-$2F) = decoded fields
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        LDX ZP_SLOT_X16
.wait_d5:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_d5
.chk_d5:
        CMP #$D5                ; Address prologue byte 1
        BNE .wait_d5
        NOP                     ; Timing adjustment
.wait_aa:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_aa
        CMP #$AA                ; Address prologue byte 2
        BNE .chk_d5             ; Retry from D5 check
        NOP
.wait_96:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_96
        EOR #$96                ; Address prologue byte 3
        BNE .chk_d5             ; Retry from D5 check

; Read 4 pairs of odd-even encoded bytes: volume, track, sector, checksum.
        LDY #$03                ; 4 bytes (Y = 3..0)
.read_pair:
        STA ZP_TEMP_B           ; Store running checksum (A=0 on first iter)
.wait_odd:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_odd
        ROL                     ; Odd byte: shift into position
        STA ZP_TEMP_A
.wait_even:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_even
        AND ZP_TEMP_A           ; Even byte: combine
        STA ZP_ADDR_VOL,Y       ; Store+Y
        EOR ZP_TEMP_B           ; Running checksum
        DEY
        BPL .read_pair

; Verify checksum (A should be 0) and DE epilogue.
        TAY
        BNE ERROR_RETURN        ; Checksum failed
.wait_de:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_de
        CMP #$DE                ; Address epilogue
        BNE ERROR_RETURN

; Shared return points: carry clear = success, carry set = error.
SUCCESS_RETURN:
        CLC                     ; Success: carry clear
        RTS

ERROR_RETURN:
        SEC                     ; Error: carry set
        RTS

; -------------------------------------------------------------------------
;  READ_DATA_FIELD
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------

READ_DATA_FIELD:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Read and decode a 6-and-2 encoded sector data field.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_SLOT_X16 -- slot * 16 for disk I/O
        ;   ZP_DEST -- destination pointer
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Scans for D5 AA AD prologue, reads 86 auxiliary nibbles
        ;   and 256 primary nibbles through the translate table at
        ;   NIBBLE_XLAT, verifies the checksum nibble and DE epilogue,
        ;   then recombines 6-bit and 2-bit portions into 256 bytes.
        ;
        ; Outputs:
        ;   Carry clear = success, carry set = error
        ;   256 bytes written to (ZP_DEST),Y
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   NIBBLE_BUF_PRI, NIBBLE_BUF_AUX
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        LDX ZP_SLOT_X16
        LDY #$18                ; Timeout counter
.wait_d5:
        DEY
        BMI ERROR_RETURN
.wait_dat:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_dat
.chk_d5:
        CMP #$D5                ; Data prologue byte 1
        BNE .wait_d5
        NOP
.wait_aa:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_aa
        CMP #$AA                ; Data prologue byte 2
        BNE .chk_d5             ; Back to CMP #$D5
.wait_ad:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_ad
        EOR #$AD                ; Data prologue byte 3
        BNE .chk_d5

; Read 86 auxiliary nibbles (2-bit portions) into NIBBLE_BUF_AUX buffer (backwards).
        PHP                     ; Save flags (Z set, A=0)
        JSR ERROR_RETURN        ; Set carry (harmless, PLP restores)
        PLP                     ; Restore Z and A=0 as XOR seed
        LDY #$56                ; 86 nibbles
.read_aux:
        STY ZP_TEMP_A
.wait_aux:
        LDY DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_aux
        EOR NIBBLE_XLAT,Y       ; Decode through translate table
        LDY ZP_TEMP_A
        DEY
        STA NIBBLE_BUF_AUX,Y   ; Store to NIBBLE_BUF_AUX buffer (backwards)
        BNE .read_aux

; Read 256 primary nibbles (6-bit portions) into NIBBLE_BUF_PRI buffer (forwards).
.read_pri:
        STY ZP_TEMP_A           ; Y=0 on first iter, then loop counter
.wait_pri:
        LDY DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_pri
        EOR NIBBLE_XLAT,Y
        LDY ZP_TEMP_A
        STA NIBBLE_BUF_PRI,Y   ; Store to NIBBLE_BUF_PRI buffer
        INY
        BNE .read_pri

; Read and verify checksum nibble.
.wait_chk:
        LDY DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_chk
        EOR NIBBLE_XLAT,Y
        BNE ERROR_RETURN        ; Checksum mismatch

; Verify DE epilogue.
.wait_epi:
        LDA DISK_DATA,X
        BPL .wait_epi
        CMP #$DE
        BNE ERROR_RETURN

; Recombine 6-and-2 encoded data into 256 bytes at.
; Auxiliary buffer has 2-bit portions, primary has 6-bit portions.
        LDY #$00
.reset_x:
        LDX #$56                ; Aux buffer index (86 entries)
.decode:
        DEX
        BMI .reset_x            ; Wrap X back to ZP_SPRITE_W when negative
        LDA NIBBLE_BUF_PRI,Y   ; 6-bit value
        LSR NIBBLE_BUF_AUX,X   ; Shift out 2 bits from aux
        ROL                     ; Bit 0 from aux
        LSR NIBBLE_BUF_AUX,X
        ROL                     ; Bit 1 from aux
        STA (ZP_DEST),Y        ; Store decoded byte
        INY
        BNE .decode
        CLC                     ; Success
        RTS

; =========================================================================
;  Seek step rate tables
; =========================================================================

SEEK_ACCEL_RATES:
        HEX 01 30 28 24 20 1E 1D 1C
SEEK_DECEL_RATES:
        HEX 70 2C 26 22 1F 1E 1D 1C

; =========================================================================
;  SEEK
; =========================================================================

SEEK:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Move disk arm to target half-track.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   A -- target half-track number
        ;   ZP_CUR_HTRK -- current half-track position
        ;   ZP_SLOT_X16 -- slot * 16 for phase soft switches
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Steps the stepper motor one half-track at a time toward
        ;   the target, using acceleration/deceleration delay tables
        ;   for smooth head movement. Turns each phase on, waits,
        ;   then turns the old phase off.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   ZP_CUR_HTRK -- updated to new position
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        STA ZP_TGT_HTRK        ; Target half-track
        LDY #$00
        STY ZP_TEMP_B           ; Acceleration index = 0
.loop:
        LDA ZP_CUR_HTRK        ; Current half-track
        STA ZP_TEMP_A           ; Save for phase-off step
        SEC
        SBC ZP_TGT_HTRK        ; Distance = current - target
        BEQ .done               ; At target
        BCS .move_in            ; Current > target: move inward
        INC ZP_CUR_HTRK        ; Current < target: step outward
        EOR #$FF                ; Negate distance (make positive)
        BCC .calc_rate          ; Always taken (carry clear from SBC)
.move_in:
        DEC ZP_CUR_HTRK        ; Step inward
        ADC #$FE                ; A = distance - 2 (carry was set)
.calc_rate:
        CMP ZP_TEMP_B           ; Compare distance with accel index
        BCC .use_dist           ; Use smaller of the two
        LDA ZP_TEMP_B
.use_dist:
        CMP #$08                ; Cap at 7
        BCS .step               ; If >= 8, use Y as-is
        TAY                     ; Y = rate index (0-7)
.step:
        SEC                     ; Carry set for ROL in SET_PHASE
        JSR SET_PHASE           ; Turn on new phase
        LDA SEEK_ACCEL_RATES,Y  ; Acceleration delay
        JSR DELAY
        LDA ZP_TEMP_A           ; Saved old half-track
        CLC                     ; Carry clear for ROL in SET_PHASE_A
        JSR SET_PHASE_A         ; Turn off old phase
        LDA SEEK_DECEL_RATES,Y  ; Deceleration delay
        JSR DELAY
        INC ZP_TEMP_B           ; Advance acceleration index
        BNE .loop               ; Always taken
.done:
        JSR DELAY               ; Final settling delay
        CLC                     ; Carry clear for final phase access

; Access a stepper motor phase. Carry selects on (SEC) or off (CLC).
; SET_PHASE uses ZP_CUR_HTRK; SET_PHASE_A takes half-track in A.
SET_PHASE:
        LDA ZP_CUR_HTRK
SET_PHASE_A:                    ; SET_PHASE_A- entry with A = half-track
        AND #$03                ; Phase 0-3
        ROL                     ; Shift: carry->bit0, makes 0/1/2/3 -> 0/1/2/3/4/5/6/7
        ORA ZP_SLOT_X16         ; Add slot offset
        TAX
        LDA DISK_PHASE0_OFF,X   ; Access phase soft switch
        RTS

; -------------------------------------------------------------------------
;  DELAY
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------

DELAY:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Delay loop (~18 cycles per outer iteration).
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   A -- number of outer-loop iterations
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Each iteration runs an 18-cycle inner loop, then
        ;   decrements A until zero.
        ; Clobbers: A, X
        LDX #$12                ; Inner loop: 18 iterations
.inner:
        DEX
        BNE .inner
        NOP
        SEC                     ; (no-op for timing)
        SBC #$01                ; Decrement outer counter
        BNE DELAY
        RTS

; -------------------------------------------------------------------------
;  SEEK_TO_TRACK
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------

SEEK_TO_TRACK:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Seek to a track with automatic motor on/off.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   A -- target track number (0-34)
        ;   ZP_CUR_HTRK -- current half-track position
        ;   ZP_SLOT_X16 -- slot * 16
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Turns motor on, converts track to half-tracks, calls
        ;   SEEK, then turns motor off.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   ZP_CUR_HTRK -- updated to new position
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y
        LDX ZP_SLOT_X16
        CMP DISK_MOTOR_ON,X     ; Turn motor on (side effect of read)
        CMP ZP_CUR_HTRK        ; Compare target with current track
        BEQ .done               ; Already there
        ASL                     ; Double to half-tracks
        ASL ZP_CUR_HTRK        ; Double current too
        JSR SEEK                ; Do the seek
        LDX ZP_SLOT_X16
.done:
        CMP DISK_MOTOR_OFF,X    ; Turn motor off
        RTS

; =========================================================================
;  READ_SECTORS
; =========================================================================

READ_SECTORS:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Read all sectors for a track group.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_TGT_TRACK -- starting track number
        ;   ZP_TBL_INDEX -- index into PAGE_TABLE
        ;   ZP_SLOT_X16 -- slot * 16
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Builds a sector dispatch table ($90-$9F) from PAGE_TABLE,
        ;   then reads sectors one at a time, matching address fields.
        ;   When all sectors for a track are done, advances to the
        ;   next track. Stops on a $00 terminator in the page table.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   ZP_SEC_TABLE ($90-$9F), ZP_TGT_TRACK, ZP_TBL_INDEX
        ;   Sector data written to pages specified by PAGE_TABLE
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; Build sector dispatch table: $90-$9F holds destination page for each sector.
        LDX #$10                ; Clear 17 entries ($90-$A0)
        LDA #$00
.clear:
        STA ZP_SEC_TABLE,X
        DEX
        BPL .clear

; Fill sector table from page table. X = sector index, Y = table offset.
        LDX #$00
.fill:
        LDY ZP_TBL_INDEX
        LDA PAGE_TABLE,Y        ; Get destination page
        BEQ .read_loop          ; $00 = end of this track's entries
        STA ZP_SEC_TABLE,X      ; Map sector X to this page
        INC ZP_TBL_INDEX        ; Advance table pointer
        INC ZP_SEC_REMAIN       ; Count sectors to read
        BEQ .read_loop          ; Overflow protection
        INX
        CPX #$10                ; Max 16 sectors per track
        BCC .fill

; Read loop: read sectors until all mapped sectors are done.
.read_loop:
        LDA ZP_TGT_TRACK       ; Seek to target track
        JSR SEEK_TO_TRACK
.retry:
        JSR READ_ADDR_FIELD     ; Read address field
        BCS .retry              ; Error: retry
        LDA ZP_ADDR_SEC         ; Sector number from disk
        STA ZP_CUR_HTRK        ; (reuse $0D as temp)
        CMP ZP_TGT_TRACK       ; Verify we're on the right track
        BNE .read_loop          ; Wrong track: re-seek
        LDX ZP_ADDR_TRK        ; Sector number (used as table index)
        LDA ZP_SEC_TABLE,X     ; Look up destination page
        BEQ .retry              ; Already read or not needed: skip
        STA ZP_DEST+1           ; Set destination page
        LDA #$00
        STA ZP_DEST             ; Destination low = $00
        JSR READ_DATA_FIELD     ; Read and decode sector data
        BCS .retry              ; Error: retry

; Mark sector as done.
        LDA #$00
        LDX ZP_ADDR_TRK
        STA ZP_SEC_TABLE,X     ; Clear entry
        DEC ZP_SEC_REMAIN       ; One fewer sector to read
        BNE .retry              ; More sectors: continue

; Track done. Check if more tracks in this group.
        INC ZP_TGT_TRACK       ; Next track
        LDY ZP_TBL_INDEX
        LDA PAGE_TABLE,Y        ; Check next entry
        BNE READ_SECTORS        ; Non-zero: more tracks to read
        RTS                     ; Done with this group

; Set target track (A) and page table offset (Y), then jump to READ_SECTORS.
SET_TRACK_AND_TABLE:
        STY ZP_TBL_INDEX
        STA ZP_TGT_TRACK
        JMP READ_SECTORS

; Seek to track A, save track in LDR_TRACK, then restore zero page from ZP_SAVE.
SEEK_AND_RESTORE_ZP:
        STA LDR_TRACK           ; Remember track position
        JSR SEEK_TO_TRACK       ; Seek (also turns motor off)
        LDX #$00
.restore:
        LDA ZP_SAVE,X           ; Restore from save area
        STA $00,X
        INX
        BNE .restore
        RTS

; Save zero page to ZP_SAVE, then fall through to LOADER_ENTRY.
SAVE_ZP:
        LDX #$00
.save:
        LDA $00,X
        STA ZP_SAVE,X
        INX
        BNE .save
        ; Fall through to LOADER_ENTRY

; Restore persistent state (track, slot) to ZP, then jump to DISPATCH.
LOADER_ENTRY:
        LDA LDR_TRACK
        STA ZP_CUR_HTRK
        LDA LDR_SLOT
        STA ZP_SLOT_X16
        JMP DISPATCH

; Padding and residual data after loader code.
        DS $51E0-*,0
        HEX 05 0A 0F 14 00 00 00 00
        HEX 56 A9 08 20 FF 56 20 00
        HEX 40 A9 00 8D F8 03 8D FF

; Track table for the 4 game-data loading phases.
; Phase 0: track 5, Phase 1: track 10, Phase 2: track 15, Phase 3: track 20.
TRACK_TABLE:
        HEX 05 0A 0F 14

; Residual data in sector (not referenced by loader code).
        HEX A9 43 8D F9
@ %def RWTS_ENTRY READ_ADDR_FIELD SUCCESS_RETURN ERROR_RETURN READ_DATA_FIELD SEEK_ACCEL_RATES SEEK_DECEL_RATES SEEK SET_PHASE SET_PHASE_A DELAY SEEK_TO_TRACK READ_SECTORS SET_TRACK_AND_TABLE SEEK_AND_RESTORE_ZP SAVE_ZP LOADER_ENTRY TRACK_TABLE

<<nibble buffers>>=

; =========================================================================
;  Nibble buffers and translate table ($5200-$53FF)
;
;  NIBBLE_BUF_PRI-$52FF: Primary nibble buffer (256 bytes, overwritten each read)
;  NIBBLE_BUF_AUX-$5355: Auxiliary nibble buffer (86 bytes, overwritten each read)
;  NIBBLE_XLAT-$53D5: 6-and-2 nibble translate table (256 bytes, persistent)
;
;  The translate table maps raw disk byte values to 6-bit values (0-63).
;  Only entries at offsets KEY_CTRL_V-$FF are valid; others are zero.
;  The table overlaps both buffers but is never overwritten by them:
;  aux writes go to NIBBLE_BUF_AUX-$5355, primary writes go to NIBBLE_BUF_PRI-$52FF,
;  and table reads go to $536C-$53D5.
; =========================================================================

        ORG $5200
NIBBLE_BUF_PRI:                 ; NIBBLE_BUF_PRI- primary nibble buffer

; Initial contents from disk (overwritten during first read).
; This data happens to partially duplicate code from $555F but is never executed.
        HEX 03 A9 6B 8D FA 03 A9 93
        HEX 8D FB 03 A9 BB 8D FC 03
        HEX AD 70 C0 A2 04 A0 00 AD
        HEX 64 C0 0D 65 C0 10 15 88
        HEX D0 F5 CA D0 F2 A9 19 85
        HEX 52 85 54 A9 62 85 53 85
        HEX 55 D0 0F 00 A9 61 85 52
        HEX A9 62 85 54 A9 C0 85 53
        HEX 85 55 A9 08 8D BA 72 AD
        HEX B4 FB C9 08 D0 0A A9 CB
        HEX 8D 22 60 A9 CC 8D 0E 60
        HEX 6C 4E 00 48 A2 00 B5 00
        HEX BC 00 57 94 00 9D 00 57
        HEX E8 D0 F3 68 60 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 05 0A 0F 14 00
        HEX 00 00 00 3C 00 00 20 20
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 20 20 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 20 20 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 20 2E 20 00 00
        HEX 00 00 20 3F 20 00 00 00
        HEX 00 20 3B 30 00 00 00 00
        HEX 20 3B 38 20 20 2A 20 22
        HEX 2E 3C 2F 21 2A 20

; Nibble translate table: maps raw disk byte values to 6-bit values.
; Spans $52D6-$53D5 (256 bytes). Only entries for disk bytes KEY_CTRL_V-$FF
; (at offsets $536C-$53D5) contain valid values 0-63.
NIBBLE_XLAT:
        HEX 22 31 3E 3F 35 20 20 22
        HEX 3F 3F
        HEX 21 3C 2A 20 20 2F 3F 3E
        HEX 3C 2A 20 20 20 26 3F 38
        HEX 00 00 20 20 20 2F 20 00
        HEX 00 00 20 20 2F 00 00 01

        ORG $5300
NIBBLE_BUF_AUX:                 ; NIBBLE_BUF_AUX- auxiliary nibble buffer
; First $6C bytes are work buffer (overwritten during reads).
; $536C-$53D5: 6-and-2 decode values (disk bytes $96-$FF -> 0-63).
; Value 0 at $536C maps disk byte $96 to decoded value 0.
; Zeros in non-$96..$FF positions indicate invalid disk bytes.
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 01 00 00
        HEX 02 03 00 04 05 06 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 07 08 00 00
        HEX 00 09 0A 0B 0C 0D 00 00
        HEX 0E 0F 10 11 12 13 00 14
        HEX 15 16 17 18 19 1A 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 1B 00 1C 1D 1E 00 00
        HEX 00 1F 00 00 20 21 00 22
        HEX 23 24 25 26 27 28 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 29 2A 2B 00 2C
        HEX 2D 2E 2F 30 31 32 00 00
        HEX 33 34 35 36 37 38 00 39
        HEX 3A 3B 3C 3D 3E 3F 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00
@ %def NIBBLE_BUF_PRI NIBBLE_XLAT NIBBLE_BUF_AUX

<<page table>>=

; =========================================================================
;  Page destination table
; =========================================================================

        ORG $5400
PAGE_TABLE:
; Track group 1-4 (offset $00): first boot loads game code/data.
        HEX 5C 5D 04 05 06 07 08 09
        HEX 0A 0B 0C 0D 0E 0F 10 11
        HEX 12 19 1A 1B 1C 1D 1E 1F
        HEX 40 41 42 43 44 45 46 47
        HEX 60 61 62 63 64 65 66 73
        HEX 74 7B 7C 7D 7E 7F 80 81
        HEX 82 83 84 85 86 87 88 89
        HEX 8A 8B 5E 5F 00 00 00 00

; Track group 5+ (offset $40): game data reload phases.
PAGE_TABLE_RELOAD:
        HEX 02 13 14 15 16 17 18 67
        HEX 68 69 6A 6B 6C 6D 6E 6F
        HEX 70 71 72 75 76 77 78 79
        HEX 7A 8C 8D 8E 8F 90 91 92
        HEX 93 94 95 96 97 98 99 9A
        HEX 9B 9C 9D 9E 9F A0 A1 A2
        HEX A3 A4 A5 A6 A7 A8 A9 AA
        HEX AB AC AD AE AF B0 B1 B2
        HEX B3 B4 B5 B6 B7 B8 B9 BA
        HEX BB BC BD 00 00 00 00 00

        DS $5500-*,0
@ %def PAGE_TABLE PAGE_TABLE_RELOAD

<<dispatch>>=

; =========================================================================
;  DISPATCH --- Main loader dispatch
; =========================================================================

        ORG $5500
DISPATCH:
        SUBROUTINE

        ; Main loader dispatch -- routes to reload or first boot.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   LDR_PHASE -- boot phase ($FF = first boot, 0-3 = reload phase)
        ;   ZP_JOY_FLAG -- bit 7 set if joystick present
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   If LDR_PHASE is $FF, jumps to FIRST_BOOT for initial setup.
        ;   Otherwise advances phase (mod 4), selects the corresponding
        ;   track from TRACK_TABLE, reads level data, and parks the head.
        ;
        ; Outputs:
        ;   LDR_PHASE -- updated phase counter
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   LDR_PHASE, disk head position
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; Check boot phase counter.
        LDX LDR_PHASE
        BPL .reload             ; >= 0: reload game data phase
        JMP FIRST_BOOT          ; $FF: first boot

; --- Reload path: load one set of game data (phases 0-3) ---
.reload:
        INX                     ; Advance phase
        TXA
        AND #$03                ; Wrap to 0-3
        TAX
        BIT ZP_JOY_FLAG        ; Check joystick present flag
        BMI .store_phase        ; If joystick present, keep phase
        LDX #$00               ; No joystick: always use phase 0
.store_phase:
        STX LDR_PHASE          ; Store new phase
        LDY #$40               ; Page table offset = $40 (reload table)
        LDA TRACK_TABLE,X      ; Get track for this phase
        JSR SET_TRACK_AND_TABLE ; Read sectors from that track
        LDA #$08               ; Park head at track 8
        JSR SEEK_AND_RESTORE_ZP
        RTS

; =========================================================================
;  FIRST_BOOT --- First-time boot sequence
; =========================================================================

FIRST_BOOT:
        SUBROUTINE

        ; First-time boot -- loads game, detects hardware, patches code.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   LDR_PHASE -- must be $FF (first boot marker)
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Phase 1: reads tracks 1-4, copies stack and VECTOR_PAGE init data.
        ;   Phase 2: loads level data from track 5, calls GAME_INIT.
        ;   Phase 3: probes paddle buttons to detect joystick; sets input
        ;     handler pointers accordingly.
        ;   Phase 4: applies Apple IIc patches if needed, restores zero
        ;     page from ZP_SAVE, and jumps to game entry via.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   LDR_PHASE, $0100-$01EF, $0300-$03EF, FLOOR_Y_TABLE,
        ;   ZP_INPUT_LO/HI_1/2, ZP_JOY_FLAG, game code patches
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; --- Phase 1: Read tracks 1-4 (main game code and data) ---
        LDA #$01               ; Starting track = 1
        LDY #$00               ; Page table offset = $00
        JSR SET_TRACK_AND_TABLE

; Copy loaded data to stack page and VECTOR_PAGE.
; The first two sectors loaded ($5C00 and STAGE_VECTORS pages) contain
; initial stack and VECTOR_PAGE data.
        LDY #$00
.copy_init:
        LDA STAGE_STACK,Y
        STA STACK_PAGE,Y       ; Stack page
        LDA STAGE_VECTORS,Y
        STA VECTOR_PAGE,Y      ; Vector page
        INY
        CPY #$F0               ; Copy 240 bytes (leave top 16 for stack)
        BCC .copy_init

; Mark first boot complete.
        INC LDR_PHASE          ; $FF -> $00

; Reset stack and load track 5.
        LDX #$FF
        TXS                    ; Reset stack pointer
        LDA #$05               ; Track 5
        LDY #$40               ; Page table offset (reload table)
        JSR SET_TRACK_AND_TABLE
        LDA #$08               ; Park head at track 8
        JSR SEEK_AND_RESTORE_ZP

; --- Phase 2: Initialize game ---
        JSR GAME_INIT

; Initialize floor Y-coordinate table (4 floors, 40 pixels apart).
        LDA #$00
        STA FLOOR_Y_TABLE       ; Entry 0: sentinel
        STA FLOOR_Y_TABLE+7     ; Entry 7: sentinel
        LDA #$43
        STA FLOOR_Y_TABLE+1     ; Floor 1: Y=67
        LDA #$6B
        STA FLOOR_Y_TABLE+2     ; Floor 2: Y=107
        LDA #$93
        STA FLOOR_Y_TABLE+3     ; Floor 3: Y=147
        LDA #$BB
        STA FLOOR_Y_TABLE+4     ; Floor 4: Y=187

; --- Phase 3: Detect joystick ---
; Read paddle buttons; if either is active (low), joystick is present.
        LDA SW_PADDLE_TRIG     ; Reset paddle timers
        LDX #$04               ; Outer timeout
        LDY #$00               ; Inner timeout
.joy_loop:
        LDA SW_PADDLE_BTN0
        ORA SW_PADDLE_BTN1
        BPL .joy_found          ; Bit 7 clear = button active = joystick
        DEY
        BNE .joy_loop
        DEX
        BNE .joy_loop

; No joystick: point input pointers to a RAM byte with bit 7 clear.
; This makes the joystick button poll always read "not pressed," so input
; falls through to the keyboard check in the attract loop.
        LDA #<KBD_DUMMY_ADDR
        STA ZP_INPUT_1
        STA ZP_INPUT_2
        LDA #>KBD_DUMMY_ADDR
        STA ZP_INPUT_1+1
        STA ZP_INPUT_2+1
        BNE .patch              ; Always taken

        BRK                    ; (dead byte, never reached)

; Joystick detected: point input pointers to hardware button registers.
.joy_found:
        LDA #<SW_PUSH_BTN0
        STA ZP_INPUT_1          ; ZP_INPUT_1 -> SW_PUSH_BTN0
        LDA #<SW_PUSH_BTN1
        STA ZP_INPUT_2          ; ZP_INPUT_2 -> SW_PUSH_BTN1
        LDA #>SW_PUSH_BTN0
        STA ZP_INPUT_1+1
        STA ZP_INPUT_2+1

; --- Phase 4: Machine-specific patches ---
.patch:
        LDA #<LIFE_LOST_HANDLER
        STA SMC_ATTRACT_EXIT_JMP ; Redirect START_ATTRACT's exit JMP
                                 ;   from ATTRACT_LOOP to LIFE_LOST_HANDLER
                                 ;   (shared code path for cold boot and
                                 ;   end-of-life).

; Check machine type for Apple IIc-specific patches.
        LDA ROM_MACHID
        CMP #MACHID_IIC         ; Apple IIc?
        BNE .restore_zp
        LDA #KEY_IIC_LEFT       ; IIc left-arrow key code
        STA SMC_KEY_LEFT        ; Patch INPUT_DISPATCH left-arrow CMP
        LDA #KEY_IIC_RIGHT      ; IIc right-arrow key code
        STA SMC_KEY_RIGHT       ; Patch INPUT_DISPATCH right-arrow CMP

; Restore zero page and jump to game.
.restore_zp:
        LDX #$00
.restore:
        LDA ZP_SAVE,X
        DC.B $9D,$00,$00        ; STA $0000,X -- must be 3-byte absolute form;
                                ;   dasm would emit 2-byte zero-page STA ZP_PAGE_FLAG,X
        INX
        BNE .restore
        JMP (ZP_GAME_ENTRY)     ; -> START_ATTRACT via ZP_SAVE

; Padding with residual data.
        DS $55F2-*,0
        HEX 05 0A 0F 14         ; Track numbers (unreferenced copy)
        DS $55FC-*,0
        HEX 04 A5 00 04         ; Residual data
@ %def DISPATCH FIRST_BOOT

\paragraph{Phase 4 game-code patches.}  After the disk load is complete
(all level data in place, joystick probe done) but before the zero-page
restore and game entry, [[FIRST_BOOT]] writes three self-modifying
operand bytes in the freshly loaded game image:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[SMC_ATTRACT_EXIT_JMP]] (the low-byte operand of the closing
  [[JMP]] in [[START_ATTRACT]]) is unconditionally rewritten to
  [[#<LIFE_LOST_HANDLER]].  The original on-disk value points at
  [[ATTRACT_LOOP]], but no real-world boot path ever takes that target:
  every cold boot lands in [[LIFE_LOST_HANDLER]] first (extras stash is
  zero, so the handler falls through to [[RESTART_NEW_GAME]], which
  runs [[GAME_START_INIT]] and then falls into [[ATTRACT_LOOP]]).  The
  on-disk [[JMP ATTRACT_LOOP]] byte sequence is kept for byte-exact
  preservation but is dead as shipped.
\item [[SMC_KEY_LEFT]] and [[SMC_KEY_RIGHT]] (the immediate operands of
  the two arrow-key [[CMP]]s in [[INPUT_DISPATCH]]) are rewritten to
  [[KEY_IIC_LEFT]] ([[$CB]]) and [[KEY_IIC_RIGHT]] ([[$CC]]) only when
  [[ROM_MACHID]] reports [[MACHID_IIC]].  These are the Apple~IIc
  keycodes emitted by its dedicated left/right arrow keys, which differ
  from the Apple~II/IIe [[$88]]/[[$95]] codes that the game was
  originally built against.  On II and IIe machines the patch is
  skipped and the CMPs keep their shipped [[KEY_LEFT]]/[[KEY_RIGHT]]
  values.
\end{itemize}

\section{Empty page and zero-page image}

[[UNUSED_PAGE]] is 256 bytes of padding between the
loader code at [[$5500]] and the on-disk zero-page image at [[$5700]].
Nothing in any shipped binary references any address in this page;
it exists because the sector layout reserves one full page for the
loader's track-dispatch table plus trailing residue, and the next
persistent byte on track~0 starts a page later.

[[ZP_SAVE]] at [[$5700]]--[[$57FF]] is the on-disk image of zero
page at cold start.  [[FIRST_BOOT]] copies this buffer byte-by-byte
into [[$0000]]--[[$00FF]] right before [[JMP (ZP_GAME_ENTRY)]] hands
control to the game.  The two bytes at offset [[$4E]]/[[$4F]]
([[ZP_GAME_ENTRY]]) are [[$A3 $72]] --- that is, [[$72A3]] =
[[START_ATTRACT]], which is why the attract loop is the first live
game code to run.

[[ZP_SAVE]] also serves as the save/restore backing when the game
re-enters the loader for a level swap: [[SAVE_ZP]] copies
[[$0000]]--[[$00FF]] back into [[ZP_SAVE]] before [[JSR LOADER_ENTRY]],
and [[SEEK_AND_RESTORE_ZP]] reloads the saved bytes before
returning to game code.  The bytes shipped on disk are therefore the
\emph{initial} state of every ZP variable; most subsequent rewrites
happen through [[INIT_LEVEL_STATE]] (which copies [[LVL_INIT_ENTITY]],
[[LVL_INIT_SPRITE]] and [[LVL_INIT_INPUT]] over ZP~[[$01]]--[[$B4]] on
each level start) or directly by the live code.

Each 8-byte row in the chunk below carries an inline comment listing
the named ZP symbols that receive non-zero seeds in that span, making
the cold-start value of every variable in the game visible at a
glance.

<<empty and zp save>>=

; =========================================================================
;  Empty page and ZP save area
; =========================================================================

        ORG $5600
UNUSED_PAGE:
        DS $100,0               ; Unused page

        ORG $5700
ZP_SAVE:
        ; 256-byte image of zero page at cold start.  Copied byte-by-byte
        ; into $00..$FF by FIRST_BOOT just before JMP (ZP_GAME_ENTRY);
        ; every ZP variable's initial value comes from here.  Also used
        ; as save/restore backing when the game re-enters the loader
        ; (SAVE_ZP writes ZP back here before LOADER_ENTRY, and
        ; SEEK_AND_RESTORE_ZP reloads it before returning to the game).
        ;
        ; The bytes are laid out in ZP offset order; each HEX row below
        ; covers an 8-byte span $00+N..$00+N+7 and the row comment lists
        ; the named ZP symbols that receive non-zero seeds in that span.

        HEX 80 00 00 06 00 00 30 00  ; $00-$07: ZP_PAGE_FLAG=$80 (skip flip),
                                     ;   ZP_PLAYER_STANCE=$06, ZP_PLAYER_COL=$30
        HEX 04 01 01 01 01 01 01 00  ; $08-$0F: ZP_SPECIAL_HP=$04,
                                     ;   ZP_BEAM_SEED_FLOOR..ZP_HIT_GATE=$01
        HEX 00 40 50 00 03 3B 63 00  ; $10-$17: ZP_COMPANION_COL=$5040 (LO,HI),
                                     ;   ZP_COMPANION_OFF=$0300,
                                     ;   ZP_COMPANION_ROW=$633B
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 FF 01 09  ; $18-$1F: ZP_ENT_RESCUED=$FF,
                                     ;   ZP_HIT_FLAG=$01 (gameplay),
                                     ;   ZP_ANIM_COUNTER=$09
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00  ; $20-$27: ZP_HIGH_SCORE_0/1/2 = $00
        HEX 00 00 20 00 00 00 27 00  ; $28-$2F: $2A=$20 (unnamed),
                                     ;   ZP_CLEAR_COL=$27
        HEX 40 FF FF FF 00 00 30 C0  ; $30-$37: $30=$40 (unnamed),
                                     ;   ZP_PROJ_MAX/GATE/COMPANION_GATE=$FF,
                                     ;   ZP_SFX_CLICK=$30 $37=$C0
                                     ;   (SW_SPEAKER hi via ZP_SFX_CLICK+1)
        HEX 30 01 00 00 00 00 00 00  ; $38-$3F: ZP_SFX_CLICK_SAVED=$30,
                                     ;   ZP_GAME_OVER=$01 (one hit credit)
        HEX 00 0B 0A 0F 00 00 00 00  ; $40-$47: ZP_HIT_MAX=$0B,
                                     ;   ZP_HIT_Y_OFFSET=$0A, ZP_HIT_Y_SPAN=$0F
        HEX 01 01 6B 02 02 00 A3 72  ; $48-$4F: ZP_INPUT_MODE=$01,
                                     ;   ZP_BTN_STATE=$01, ZP_PLAYER_Y=$6B,
                                     ;   ZP_WALK_FRAME=$02, ZP_SPRITE_XREF=$02,
                                     ;   ZP_GAME_ENTRY=$72A3 (= START_ATTRACT)
        HEX 00 00 61 C0 62 C0 00 00  ; $50-$57: ZP_INPUT_1=$C061 (SW_PUSH_BTN0),
                                     ;   ZP_INPUT_2=$C062 (SW_PUSH_BTN1)
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 04 03  ; $58-$5F: ZP_LIVES_BCD=$04 (four lives),
                                     ;   ZP_PRNG_A=$03
        HEX 22 4A 70 90 B6 DE 56 DA  ; $60-$67: per-floor Y-threshold table
        HEX 2A 56 82 6C AE 2A 98 C4  ; $68-$6F: (12-entry floor seed)
        HEX 40 C4 43 6B 93 93 93 6B  ; $70-$77: per-floor row anchors
        HEX 6B 43 43 43 6B 93 00 24  ; $78-$7F: (FLOOR_THRESH family at $70)
        HEX 48 70 98 00 30 58 80 A8  ; $80-$87: scratch seeds for draw params
        HEX 7C 01 01 01 00 FF FF FF  ; $88-$8F: ZP_SPRITE_BLOCK start ($7C),
                                     ;   ZP_EXTRA_LIVES=$00
        HEX BC AB AB FF 56 00 58 00  ; $90-$97: per-slot hit-entity state
        HEX 55 00 00 00 00 00 00 00  ; $98-$9F: ZP_ENEMY_FLAG (4 slots) = $00
        HEX DF ED EF F7 00 0C 08 18  ; $A0-$A7: scratch pointer pair $A0-$A3,
                                     ;   ZP_ENEMY_Y (4 slots) at $A3
        HEX 08 00 00 01 3E 00 4D 00  ; $A8-$AF: ZP_SPECIAL_STATE=$01,
                                     ;   ZP_SPECIAL_POS=$003E, ZP_SPECIAL_ROW=$4D
        HEX 00 01 FF 01 01 FF FF FF  ; $B0-$B7: ZP_COMPANION_STATE=$01,
                                     ;   ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR=$FF (idle),
                                     ;   ZP_ENEMY_C_SND_CTR=$FF (idle)
        HEX FF 00 48 92 DA 84 83 81  ; $B8-$BF: ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR=$FF (idle)
        HEX 80 80 01 03 04 00 00 00  ; $C0-$C7: ZP_PROJ_DIR (4 slots) = $00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00  ; $C8-$CF: ZP_PROJ_X/Y = $00
        HEX 00 00 00 00 01 52 03 4E  ; $D0-$D7: ZP_SCORE_HI/MID/LO=$00,
                                     ;   ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE=$01,
                                     ;   ZP_ENEMY_C_POS=$0352, ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW=$4E
        HEX 88 CC EE FF 01 61 03 55  ; $D8-$DF: ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE=$01,
                                     ;   ZP_ENEMY_A_POS=$0361, ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW=$55
        HEX 01 04 03 80 FF 11 14 16  ; $E0-$E7: ZP_ENEMY_B_STATE=$01,
                                     ;   ZP_ENEMY_B_POS=$0304, ZP_ENEMY_B_ROW=$80,
                                     ;   ZP_ENEMY_B_SND_CTR=$FF (idle)
        HEX 18 6A 6A 6A 6A 02 02 01  ; $E8-$EF: ZP_ATTRACT_ENT_Y (4 slots, $E9-$EC)
        HEX 01 1A 14 83 75 0C 02 01  ; $F0-$F7: attract-mode scratch
        HEX D0 00 00 00 00 00 00 00  ; $F8-$FF: ZP_BEAM_TICK=$D0 (idle),
                                     ;   ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR=$00,
                                     ;   ZP_FRAME_COUNTER=$00
@ %def UNUSED_PAGE ZP_SAVE

