\section{Sector-image residue at [[SECTOR_RESIDUE_47XX]]--[[$47FF]]}

The 237 bytes at [[SECTOR_RESIDUE_47XX]]--[[$47FF]] are \emph{dead residue} from the disk
build process, not a continuation of the HUD-frame unpacker.  Three
independent lines of evidence identify them as unreachable:

\begin{enumerate}
\item \textbf{No static call or jump targets them.}  An exhaustive scan
of all five reference binaries ([[boot1.bin]], [[loader.bin]],
[[rwts.bin]], [[drol.bin]], [[level1.bin]]) for JSR~([[$20]]), JMP-abs
([[$4C]]), and JMP-indirect ([[$6C]]) with a 2-byte operand in
[[SECTOR_RESIDUE_47XX]]--[[$47FF]] returns zero hits.  No immediate load of the page byte
[[$47]] into a pointer appears anywhere either, so the region cannot
be reached via a runtime-built vector.
\item \textbf{The code is truncated mid-instruction at a page
boundary.}  Disassembly of [[$474E]] onward reads as the prologue and
first 13 iterations of [[INTERLACE_BLIT_P1]] ([[INTERLACE_BLIT_P1]]--[[$05FF]]), with
the 13th iteration cut off at [[$47FF]] (the last store is
[[STA $3528,X]] with the third operand byte landing at [[$4800]]).
The following 5120 bytes [[$4800]]--[[$5BFF]] are all [[$00]], which would
dispatch as [[BRK]] instructions --- not a continuation any real
routine could return from.
\item \textbf{The bytes are a verbatim copy of [[$0513]]--[[$05FF]].}
Byte-for-byte, [[reference/drol.bin[$4713..$47FF]]] equals
[[reference/drol.bin[$0513..$05FF]]].  The leading [[$0B]] at [[SECTOR_RESIDUE_47XX]]
matches the high byte of [[JSR INTERLACE_FILL_P2]]'s operand at
[[$0512]]--[[$0513]] --- this is mid-instruction residue, not a purposeful
constant.  The body replicates [[CLEAR_PAGE2]]'s interlace tail,
[[CLEAR_PAGE2_TEXT_ENTRY]]'s text-restore loop, and the first half
of [[INTERLACE_BLIT_P1]], all at the same offsets.
\end{enumerate}

The mechanism is incidental: the page table ([[PAGE_TABLE]]) maps track~2 sector~15 to destination page [[$47]], and track~1
sector~3 to destination page [[$05]].  These two disk sectors happen
to contain identical bytes (the build artefact of some earlier
editing pass or a deliberate sector-level duplicate).  Because
[[SECTOR_RESIDUE_47XX]]--[[$47FF]] sits after the [[HUD_FRAME_DATA]] stream terminator
at [[$4712]], the unpacker stops before reaching it, and nothing else
calls in --- so the residue has no runtime effect.

Confirmed further by [[reference/level1.bin]], built by replaying
the loader's reload-phase track read (tracks 5--9, which do not
target page~[[$47]]): it has [[$00]] throughout [[$4700]]--[[$47FF]].  The only
reason the residue appears in [[drol.bin]] is that the extracted
image was captured after the first-boot load, before the phase-0
reload cleared those pages.

Because the data is meaningless (neither executable game logic nor
displayable art), \emph{no figure is rendered} for this region.
The chunk is emitted as raw [[HEX]] to preserve byte-perfect
assembly against [[reference/drol.bin]].

