@ \chapter{Input system}

\section{Input dispatcher}

[[INPUT_DISPATCH]] handles keyboard and joystick input during
gameplay. If [[ZP_INPUT_MODE]] is negative, it delegates to
[[JOYSTICK_HANDLER]]. Otherwise it reads the keyboard and processes
five keys:

\begin{itemize}
\item Right arrow ([[KEY_RIGHT]]): enable [[DO_MOVE_RIGHT]], disable [[DO_MOVE_LEFT]]
\item Left arrow ([[KEY_LEFT]]): enable [[DO_MOVE_LEFT]], disable [[DO_MOVE_RIGHT]]
\item `A' ([[KEY_ACTION]]): fire/ascend --- enable [[DO_ASCEND]], disable [[DO_DESCEND]],
  search for a rescuable entity within range
\item `Z' ([[KEY_DESCEND]]): descend --- enable [[DO_DESCEND]], disable [[DO_ASCEND]],
  search for a rescuable entity, advance [[ZP_PLAYER_COL]]
\item Space ([[KEY_JUMP]]): set [[ZP_JUMP_FLAG]] to [[$FF]]
\end{itemize}

Direction keys work by patching the opcode byte of the movement slots in
the main loop: [[OPCODE_JSR]] to enable, [[OPCODE_BIT]] to disable.

<<drol input defines>>=

; --- Input constants ---
KEY_RIGHT       = $95           ; Right arrow key code
KEY_LEFT        = $88           ; Left arrow key code
KEY_ACTION      = $C1           ; 'A' key code (fire/ascend)
KEY_DESCEND     = $DA           ; 'Z' key code (descend)
KEY_JUMP        = $A0           ; Space key code (jump)
OPCODE_JSR      = $20           ; JSR opcode (enable direction)
OPCODE_BIT      = $2C           ; BIT abs opcode (disable direction)

; --- Zero-page state shared with the movement action handlers ---
; ZP_ASC_FLOOR / ZP_DSC_FLOOR / ZP_DSC_DIR / ZP_ENT_RESCUED are
; seeded by INPUT_DO_ASCEND / INPUT_DO_DESCEND and consumed by
; DO_ASCEND / DO_DESCEND at $6378.
ZP_ASC_FLOOR    = $0B           ; Ascent-target floor index (0..5);
                                ; set by INPUT_DO_ASCEND, read by DO_ASCEND
                                ; to index FLOOR_CEIL and FLOOR_THRESH
ZP_FLOOR_MIRROR = $0A           ; Second floor-index mirror (held in sync
                                ; with ZP_BEAM_SEED_FLOOR / ZP_ASC_FLOOR
                                ; / ZP_DSC_FLOOR on landing)
ZP_DSC_FLOOR    = $0C           ; Descent-target floor index (0..5);
                                ; set by INPUT_DO_DESCEND, read by DO_DESCEND
ZP_DSC_DIR      = $0D           ; Descent search direction: $FF = searching
                                ; down from current, $01 = just landed
                                ; (set by INPUT_DO_ASCEND / DO_DESCEND)
ZP_ENT_RESCUED  = $1D           ; Entity-rescued / post-hit flag: $FF when
                                ; a rescue has just succeeded or a hit
                                ; landed; consumed by DRAW_PLAYER and by
                                ; MR_HIT_SLIDE / ML_HIT_SLIDE

; --- Hit-entity world-Y table (12 slots, $66,X) ---
; Parallel to ENTITY_HIT_STATE ($8D) and ENTITY_HIT_ROW ($72).
; Read by INPUT_DO_ASCEND / INPUT_DO_DESCEND (to find a rescue
; candidate matching the player's Y) and by REFRESH_HIT_ENTITIES
; (to derive the on-screen column).
ENTITY_HIT_Y    = $66           ; Hit-entity world-Y ($66,X, X<=ZP_HIT_MAX)

; --- Game code stubs (referenced by input) ---
