\section{Speaker-click delay helpers}

[[SND_DELAY_DOWN]] and [[SND_DELAY_UP]] are a paired couple of
sliding-pitch speaker-click emitters.  They take a starting pitch
in [[A]] and a click count in [[X]], and emit [[X]] speaker clicks
with the per-click interval shrinking (down) or growing (up) by one
unit per iteration --- producing the descending and ascending
chirps used all over Drol's sound code.

The speaker toggle is performed via the [[ZP_SFX_CLICK]] indirect
pointer: [[CMP (ZP_SFX_CLICK),Y]] with [[Y]]=[[$00]] reads from
[[$C0XX]] where [[XX]]=[[ZP_SFX_CLICK]].  With [[ZP_SFX_CLICK]]
seeded to [[$30]], that is [[SW_SPEAKER]] (the speaker toggle
soft-switch); with [[ZP_SFX_CLICK]] seeded to [[$20]], the read hits
[[SW_CASSOUT]] (cassette-out, unused) and is effectively silent ---
the mechanism Ctrl-S uses to mute the game.

Per iteration:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[A]] := [[A]] $\mp$ [[$01]] (descending/ascending pitch delta).
\item Inner busy loop [[DEY]]/[[BNE]] burns [[A-1]] delay iterations
  ([[Y]] starts at the pre-shift pitch).
\item [[CMP (ZP_SFX_CLICK),Y]] with [[Y]]=[[$00]] reads the
  [[ZP_SFX_CLICK]] target address --- this is the click itself
  ([[SW_SPEAKER]] toggles the speaker coil).
\item [[DEX]]/[[BNE]] --- loop until the caller-specified click
  count runs out.
\end{itemize}

Callers pass tuned [[A]]/[[X]] pairs for every per-frame click
effect in the game: enemy spawn clicks, projectile emission,
footsteps, the row-copy whistle, etc.  Because the delta is
unsigned, callers needing a long falling tone choose [[A]] larger
than [[X]] so [[A]] never wraps below zero during the emission.

<<snd delay down>>=

        ORG $1091
SND_DELAY_DOWN:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Speaker-click emitter with descending pitch.  Emits X
        ; speaker clicks, with the delay before each click one unit
        ; shorter than the previous (so the perceived pitch rises).
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   A   --- starting pitch / delay unit count.  Must be >= X
        ;           so the inner counter never wraps past zero.
        ;   X   --- click count (outer iteration count).
        ;   ZP_SFX_CLICK       --- speaker-click pointer low byte
        ;           (#<SW_SPEAKER = click; #<SW_CASSOUT = silent).
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Loop X times: save pitch to Y, decrement A by 1 (shrinks
        ;   next iteration's delay), burn Y cycles of the inner
        ;   DEY/BNE loop, then read $C0XX via (ZP_SFX_CLICK),Y with
        ;   Y=0 -- this is the speaker click.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

        TAY                             ; Y <- current pitch
        SEC
        SBC #$01                        ; A <- A - 1 (descending)
.inner:
        DEY                             ; Busy delay: Y cycles
        BNE .inner
        CMP (ZP_SFX_CLICK),Y            ; Speaker click: reads $C0XX
                                        ; with Y=$00 -> toggles speaker
        DEX
        BNE SND_DELAY_DOWN              ; Outer: loop for X clicks
        RTS
@ %def SND_DELAY_DOWN

<<snd delay up>>=

        ORG $109E
SND_DELAY_UP:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Speaker-click emitter with ascending pitch.  Mirror of
        ; SND_DELAY_DOWN: emits X speaker clicks, with the delay
        ; before each click one unit longer than the previous (so
        ; the perceived pitch falls).
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   A   --- starting pitch / delay unit count.
        ;   X   --- click count (outer iteration count).
        ;   ZP_SFX_CLICK       --- speaker-click pointer low byte.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Identical to SND_DELAY_DOWN but A increments instead of
        ;   decrements each iteration.  Because the delay grows as
        ;   the loop progresses, the click interval lengthens and
        ;   the perceived pitch descends.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

        TAY                             ; Y <- current pitch
        CLC
        ADC #$01                        ; A <- A + 1 (ascending delay
                                        ; -> descending pitch)
.inner:
        DEY                             ; Busy delay: Y cycles
        BNE .inner
        CMP (ZP_SFX_CLICK),Y            ; Speaker click
        DEX
        BNE SND_DELAY_UP
        RTS
@ %def SND_DELAY_UP

\section{Beam subsystem: target controller}

[[BEAM_TARGET_TICK]] is the state machine for the player's
laser-beam subsystem.  Together with [[BEAM_TARGET_DRAW]] and
[[BEAM_UPDATE]] it implements a vertical beam that descends between
floors, telegraphs its target, and sprays short-lived horizontal
tracers from slots on each floor it crosses.  All three routines are
called only from [[BEAM_UPDATE]], which is itself gated on
[[ZP_PROJ_GATE]] ($32)~--- difficulty tier ``standard'' or ``maximum''
(score $\geq$~10000).

The beam is tracked by a pair of bytes on page~2:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[BEAM_STATE]]: [[$00]] idle, [[$0]]X active-chase, [[$F]]X
  active-attack (X~=~target floor index, 0--4).  The attack-phase
  flag is set by [[ORA #$F0]], which lights bits 4--7; only bit~7
  is tested by the dispatcher (BMI), but the low nibble still
  holds the floor index and the high nibble is masked with
  [[AND #$0F]] before indexing [[FLOOR_Y_TABLE]].
\item [[BEAM_Y]]: current scanning Y-coordinate (Apple II hi-res
  row, 0~=~top, 191~=~bottom).  Chase decreases [[BEAM_Y]]
  (beam climbs on-screen), attack increases it (beam descends).
\end{itemize}

[[BEAM_TARGET_TICK]] advances that state machine one step:

\begin{enumerate}
\item If the sound counter [[ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR]] is non-negative,
  play the next note of the post-hit jingle from [[BEAM_JINGLE]]
  and decrement the counter (falls through regardless).
\item If [[BEAM_STATE]] has bit~7 set (``attack'' phase), extract
  the target floor index ([[AND #$0F]]).  If [[BEAM_Y]] equals
  [[FLOOR_Y_TABLE]]$[{\rm X}]$, the beam has arrived: clear
  [[BEAM_STATE]].  Otherwise [[BEAM_Y]]~+=~2 (descends toward
  floor), play a pitch-[[$10]] descending click via
  [[SND_DELAY_DOWN]].
\item Else if [[BEAM_STATE]] is nonzero (``chase'' phase), take
  [[BEAM_STATE]] as the target floor index~X.  If
  [[FLOOR_CEIL]]$[{\rm X}]$\,$+$\,$1$ equals [[BEAM_Y]], the
  beam has reached the ceiling: flip to attack phase
  ([[BEAM_STATE]]~$\leftarrow$~[[BEAM_STATE]] \,[[ORA]]\,
  [[$F0]]).  Otherwise [[BEAM_Y]]~$-=$~2 (climbs toward ceiling),
  play a pitch-[[$10]] ascending click via [[SND_DELAY_UP]].
\item Else (idle): if [[ZP_BEAM_TICK]] is non-zero, RTS.  When
  it reaches~0, seed a new target:
  [[BEAM_Y]]~$\leftarrow$~[[FLOOR_Y_TABLE]]$[{\rm X}]$ and
  [[BEAM_STATE]]~$\leftarrow$~X, where~X =
  [[ZP_BEAM_SEED_FLOOR]]~--- the player-floor index captured by
  the ASCEND/DESCEND handlers when the player last anchored on a
  floor.
\end{enumerate}

[[ZP_BEAM_SEED_FLOOR]] ($09) is one of four parallel floor-index
mirrors ($09/$0A/$0B/$0C) maintained by the player-movement
handlers.  Each subsystem reads a different mirror; the beam
reads~$09 exclusively.

<<beam target tick>>=

        ORG $1230
BEAM_TARGET_TICK:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; One-frame advance of the beam target state machine.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR ($F9) --- post-hit jingle counter
        ;                             (>=0 plays the next BEAM_JINGLE note).
        ;   BEAM_STATE             --- $00 idle, $0X chase, $FX attack.
        ;   BEAM_Y                 --- current beam scan Y.
        ;   ZP_BEAM_TICK ($F8)     --- idle-phase seed gate (0 seeds beam).
        ;   ZP_BEAM_SEED_FLOOR ($09) --- floor index to seed on activation.
        ;   FLOOR_Y_TABLE          --- per-floor walk-row Y anchor.
        ;   FLOOR_CEIL             --- per-floor ceiling Y anchor
        ;                             (chase-phase exit trigger).
        ;   BEAM_JINGLE            --- post-hit jingle pitch table.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Jingle block runs first (plays one note per frame until
        ;   ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR underflows, independent of BEAM_STATE).
        ;   Then dispatches on BEAM_STATE:
        ;     bit 7 set -> attack: BEAM_Y += 2 toward FLOOR_Y_TABLE[X];
        ;                  on arrival, BEAM_STATE <- #$00 (idle).
        ;     nonzero   -> chase:  BEAM_Y -= 2 toward FLOOR_CEIL[X]+1;
        ;                  on arrival, BEAM_STATE |= #$F0 (attack).
        ;     zero      -> idle:   when ZP_BEAM_TICK == 0, seed beam
        ;                  from ZP_BEAM_SEED_FLOOR (state <- floor idx,
        ;                  Y <- FLOOR_Y_TABLE[floor idx]).
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   BEAM_Y, BEAM_STATE, ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; --- Post-hit jingle tick (runs every call while counter active) ---
        LDX ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR             ; armed if >= 0
        BMI .dispatch                   ; $FF (idle): skip jingle
        LDA BEAM_JINGLE,X               ; A = next note pitch
        DEX
        STX ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR             ; ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR -= 1
        LDX #$0A                        ; click-count
        JSR SND_DELAY_UP                ; play pitch A, 10 clicks ascending

; --- Dispatch on BEAM_STATE ---
.dispatch:
        LDA BEAM_STATE
        BMI .attack                     ; bit 7 set: attack phase
        BNE .chase                      ; nonzero: chase phase

; --- Idle: wait for tick counter, then seed ---
        LDA ZP_BEAM_TICK
        BEQ .seed                       ; 0: time to seed a new beam
        RTS                             ; still counting down

.seed:
        LDX ZP_BEAM_SEED_FLOOR          ; target floor from player mirror
        LDA FLOOR_Y_TABLE,X
        STA BEAM_Y                      ; BEAM_Y <- floor walk anchor
        STX BEAM_STATE                  ; BEAM_STATE <- floor idx (chase)
        RTS

; --- Attack phase: descend toward target floor ---
.attack:
        AND #$0F                        ; extract floor idx from state
        TAX
        LDA BEAM_Y
        CMP FLOOR_Y_TABLE,X
        BNE .attack_step                ; not yet at floor row
        LDA #$00
        STA BEAM_STATE                  ; BEAM_STATE <- idle (arrived)
        RTS
.attack_step:
        CLC
        ADC #$02                        ; BEAM_Y += 2 (descend on-screen)
        STA BEAM_Y
        LDA #$10                        ; pitch
        LDX #$0A                        ; click count
        JSR SND_DELAY_DOWN              ; descending click
        RTS

; --- Chase phase: ascend toward floor ceiling ---
.chase:
        TAX                             ; X = floor idx (BEAM_STATE low nibble)
        LDY FLOOR_CEIL,X
        INY                             ; Y = FLOOR_CEIL[X] + 1
        CPY BEAM_Y
        BNE .chase_step                 ; not yet at ceiling
        TXA
        ORA #$F0                        ; set bits 4-7 -> attack phase
        STA BEAM_STATE
        RTS
.chase_step:
        LDA BEAM_Y
        SEC
        SBC #$02                        ; BEAM_Y -= 2 (ascend on-screen)
        STA BEAM_Y
        LDA #$10                        ; pitch
        LDX #$0A                        ; click count
        JSR SND_DELAY_UP                ; ascending click
        RTS
@ %def BEAM_TARGET_TICK

\section{Beam subsystem: target draw and collision}

[[BEAM_TARGET_DRAW]] renders a short vertical sprite trail
between [[BEAM_Y]] and the current target floor's Y, then checks the
four tracked enemies for collision with that trail.

\begin{enumerate}
\item If [[BEAM_STATE]] is~[[$00]], RTS.
\item Compute $\Delta Y$~=~[[FLOOR_Y_TABLE]]$[{\rm state\_lo}]
  - $~[[BEAM_Y]].  If zero, RTS.  Clamp to 4 if $\geq$~5, otherwise
  use the raw delta as sprite height.
\item Draw [[BEAM_SPR]] via [[DRAW_SPRITE]], using
  width~2, height~$\Delta Y$, column~[[$24]], Y~=~[[BEAM_Y]].  (The
  source-pointer operands [[SMC_DS_SRC_LO]]/[[SMC_DS_SRC_HI]] are
  patched to [[BEAM_SPR]].)
\item For each of four enemy slots X~=~3..0: if [[ZP_ENEMY_FLAG]],X
  is zero, skip.  Otherwise fetch [[ZP_ENEMY_COL]],X as an index into
  [[PROJ_SCREEN_COL]] and require the screen column to be in
  $([[$23]], [[$25]]]$ (i.e.\ $\{[[$24]], [[$25]]\}$).  If so, require
  [[BEAM_Y]]~$<$~[[ZP_ENEMY_Y]],X~$\le$~[[BEAM_Y]]~$+$~[[$03]]: a
  \emph{hit} zeros the enemy flag, clears [[BEAM_STATE]], re-arms
  the post-hit jingle ([[ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR]]~$\leftarrow$~[[$0A]]), and
  awards [[$0100]]~BCD points via [[SCORE_ADD]].
\end{enumerate}

The ZP symbols [[ZP_ENEMY_FLAG]]/[[ZP_ENEMY_COL]]/[[ZP_ENEMY_Y]] introduced here
are four-slot
parallel tables for enemies tracked by the beam.  These overlap the
ESC-key location at [[$9B]] (renamed here from [[KEY_ESC]] for the
purposes of this subsystem; the ESC-key alias only aliases [[$9B]] when
the input dispatcher polls it).

\paragraph{Beam sprite and ready-prompt.}  [[BEAM_SPR]] is sprite
id~0 of the general [[SPRITE_TABLE_LO]] / [[SPRITE_TABLE_HI]] family
(the main 128-entry sprite pointer table shared by attract, enemy-B,
and UI draws).  The adjacent id~1 entry is the
``ready'' prompt sprite drawn at the top of each level intro by
[[LEVEL_INTRO_TICK]].  Both live in the swappable level-data region
and are shown in Figure~\ref{fig:sprite_table_ui} --- the beam's
sprite bytes are the first [[$0C]] bytes at [[BEAM_SPR]] and render as a
short vertical dashed trail; the ready-prompt sprite is
$[[$04]]\times[[$0F]]$ (W=[[$03]], H=[[$0F]]).

\begin{figure}[H]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=0.35\textwidth]{images/sprite_table_ui.png}
\caption{[[SPRITE_TABLE]] UI sprites.  Left: the beam sprite at id~0
([[BEAM_SPR]]), drawn by [[BEAM_TARGET_DRAW]] as a variable-height trail
1..4~rows tall between [[BEAM_Y]] and the target floor.  Right: the
