\section{Sprite pointer tables ([[$7500]]--[[$76FF]])}

The [[$7500]]--[[$76FF]] region is a 512-byte block of 16-bit sprite
pointer tables, arranged as two parallel 256-byte halves: the low-byte
half at [[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_LO]] and the high-byte half at
[[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_HI]].  For every table entry at
[[LO+$XX]] there is a matching high byte at [[HI+$XX]]; callers load
the pair to form a 16-bit sprite-data address which they then patch
into a [[DRAW_SPRITE*]] SMC source-pointer slot.

\paragraph{Table layout.}  The low-byte half is subdivided into 37
separate pointer tables ordered by subsystem.  Each sub-table is
indexed either by a 7-entry perspective-frame index (from
[[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]]) or by a pose/direction offset.  The high-byte
half at [[$7600]] mirrors the layout byte-for-byte with page-high
bytes instead of low bytes.  A single-byte null pad
([[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_LO_PAD]]) occupies [[$75FF]]; its twin
[[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_HI_PAD]] is also [[$00]].  These
pads are never indexed at runtime.

\paragraph{Sub-tables by subsystem.}  The named sub-tables are:

\begin{itemize}
\item \emph{Playfield chrome} --- [[PILLAR_SPR_LO]]/[[HI]] (7),
  [[FLOOR_SPR_LO]]/[[HI]] (11), [[WALL_L_SPR_LO]]/[[HI]] (7),
  [[WALL_SPR_LO]]/[[HI]] (7), [[HIT_SPR_NEG_LO]]/[[HI]] (7),
  [[HIT_SPR_POS_LO]]/[[HI]] (7).  Driven by the
  [[REFRESH_*]] routines and [[REFRESH_HIT_ENTITIES]].
\item \emph{Player body} --- [[PLAYER_SPR_IDLE_LO]]/[[HI]] (10),
  [[PLAYER_SPR_ACTIVE_LO]]/[[HI]] (10) for [[DRAW_PLAYER]];
  [[PLAYER_GRID_SPR_A_LO]]/[[HI]] (7) and [[PLAYER_GRID_SPR_B_LO]]/[[HI]]
  (7) for [[DRAW_ENTITIES]] phase~2 (flicker A/B selected by
  [[ZP_FRAME_COUNTER]] bit~2).
\item \emph{Special slot} --- [[SPECIAL_BODY_POSE0_LO]]/[[HI]]..[[POSE3_LO]]/[[HI]]
  (7 each) for [[SPECIAL_DRAW]]'s SMC walk cycle;
  [[SPECIAL_PEEK_LO]]/[[HI]] (1) for [[SPECIAL_INACTIVE_DRAW]];
  [[SPECIAL_GRID_SPR_A_LO]]/[[HI]] (7) and
  [[SPECIAL_GRID_SPR_B_LO]]/[[HI]] (7) for [[DRAW_ENTITIES]] phase~3.
\item \emph{Companion slot} --- [[COMPANION_NEG_POSE1_LO]]/[[HI]]..[[NEG_POSE3_LO]]/[[HI]]
  and [[COMPANION_POS_POSE1_LO]]/[[HI]]..[[POS_POSE3_LO]]/[[HI]] (7 each,
  6 poses $\times$ 2 directions) for [[COMPANION_UPDATE]]'s SMC walk cycle;
  [[COMPANION_GRID_SPR_LO]]/[[HI]] (8) for [[DRAW_ENTITIES]] phase~4.
\item \emph{Enemy-C (target creature)} --- [[ENEMY_C_TAIL_LO]]/[[HI]]
  (9 frames) for [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]]'s main tail draw;
  [[ENEMY_C_PUFF_LO]]/[[HI]] (1) and [[ENEMY_B_PUFF_LO]]/[[HI]] (1) for
  the drift-mode puff sprites of [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]] and [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]].
\item \emph{Floor enemies} --- [[FLOOR_ENEMY_SPR_S0_LO]]/[[HI]]..[[S3_LO]]/[[HI]]
  (7 each, 4 slots $\times$ 7 frames) for [[FLOOR_ENEMY_DRAW]].
\item \emph{Entity grid} --- [[ENTITY_GRID_SPR_LO]]/[[HI]] (7) for
  [[DRAW_ENTITIES]] phase~5 (20-slot entity list).
\item \emph{Rescue children} --- [[RESCUE_SPR_NEG_END_LO]]/[[HI]],
  [[RESCUE_SPR_NEG_MID_LO]]/[[HI]], [[RESCUE_SPR_POS_END_LO]]/[[HI]],
  [[RESCUE_SPR_POS_MID_LO]]/[[HI]] (7 each) for [[RESCUE_DRAW]].
\item \emph{Projectiles (right-moving only)} ---
  [[PROJ_SPR_R_LO]]/[[PROJ_SPR_R_HI]] (8) for [[HAZARD_CHECK]]; the
  left-moving twin [[PROJ_SPR_L_LO]]/[[PROJ_SPR_L_HI]] lives in the
  swappable region.
\end{itemize}

\paragraph{Targets of the pointers.}  Every pointer entry targets
either the immediately-following sprite pixel data region
[[SPRITE_PIXEL_DATA]] at [[$7700]]--[[$8BFF]] (for the playfield-chrome,
player-idle/active, and hit sprites that are part of the persistent
[[drol.bin]]), or a per-level address in the swappable region
[[$8C00]]--[[$BDFF]] (for the animated grid / body / floor-enemy
sprites, whose art changes from level to level).  This split lets
per-level levels change enemy/companion/rescue sprite art while the
playfield-chrome stays fixed.

