\section{Sprite pixel data ([[$7700]]--[[$8BFF]])}

The [[$7700]]--[[$8BFF]] region is 5376 bytes of sprite pixel data ---
the actual hi-res byte patterns referenced by the pointer tables at
[[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_LO]]/[[HI]].  Because the pointers from the
first half of the block ([[PILLAR_SPR]]..[[HIT_SPR_POS]]) land inside
this range, the playfield-chrome / hit / player-idle / player-active
sprite art lives here as part of the persistent [[drol.bin]].  The
grid-body, floor-enemy, companion, rescue and special-body tables
instead point into the swappable [[$8C00]]--[[$BDFF]] range (loaded
separately per level) so their art can vary.

\paragraph{Frame sizes.}  Each sprite frame occupies a fixed number of
bytes depending on its kind.  The playfield chrome frames (pillar,
wall, floor) take [[$8C]], [[$8C]], and [[$28]] bytes per frame
respectively; the [[HIT_SPR_*]] frames are [[$28]] bytes (roughly
2~bytes wide by 20~rows tall including padding); the player-body
frames are [[$4C]] bytes; the compact hit markers are [[$28]] bytes.
See the individual [[DRAW_SPRITE*]]-ing routines for the
exact [[ZP_SPRITE_W]] / [[ZP_SPRITE_H]] values each caller sets before
the blit.

\paragraph{Decomposition progress.}  Per-frame rendering is now
complete for all sub-tables in the range.  Three playfield-chrome
sub-tables share the $\$8\mathrm{C}$-byte, 4-column $\times$ 35-row
column-major [[INTERLACE_BLIT]] format:
[[PILLAR_SPR_DATA]] ([[$7700]]--[[$7AD3]], 7 frames),
[[WALL_L_SPR_DATA]] ([[$7DA4]]--[[$8177]], 7 frames) and
[[WALL_SPR_DATA]] ([[$8178]]--[[$854B]], 7 frames).  The
hit/floor/player sub-tables in between and after use the
[[DRAW_SPRITE_OPAQUE]] stride format instead:
[[HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_0]]--[[HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_6]] and
[[FLOOR_SPR_DATA_0]]--[[FLOOR_SPR_DATA_10]] ([[$7AD4]]--[[$7DA3]], both
$\$28$ bytes per frame),
[[PLAYER_SPR_IDLE_DATA_0]]--[[PLAYER_SPR_IDLE_DATA_8]] ([[$854C]]--
[[$87F7]], 9~unique frames at $\$4\mathrm{C}$ bytes each),
[[PLAYER_SPR_ACTIVE_DATA_0]]--[[PLAYER_SPR_ACTIVE_DATA_8]]
([[$87F8]]--[[$8ABF]], 2~frames at $\$4\mathrm{C}$ plus 7~frames at
$\$50$ bytes), [[HIT_SPR_POS_DATA_0]]--[[HIT_SPR_POS_DATA_6]]
([[$8AC0]]--[[$8BD7]], $\$28$ bytes per frame) and
[[PLAYER_GRID_SPR_A_DATA_0]]--[[PLAYER_GRID_SPR_A_DATA_4]]
([[$8BD8]]--[[$8BFF]], first 5 entries of the grid-A table before the
persistent/level-swap boundary).

