sized and formatted identically to the pillar frames: 140 bytes each,
4 columns $\times$ 35 rows, column-major, painted by
[[INTERLACE_BLIT_P1]] / [[INTERLACE_BLIT_P2]] into three perspective
bands simultaneously (rows 72--106, 112--146, 152--186).

\paragraph{Visible content.}  Each tile renders a short vertical wall
section with a torch/handle decoration on its left side.  The animation
cycles through two families of frames: frames 0--3 use green as the
primary hue while frames 4--6 use purple, so alternating between the
two families produces the pulsing ``switch-on'' effect seen when the
player triggers a tier change.  The walking-animation frame index
[[ZP_SPRITE_XREF]] advances once per footfall, keeping the wall
shimmer in phase with the player and the pillars.

