\section{WALL\_SPR frames ([[$8178]]--[[$854B]])}

[[WALL_SPR_DATA_0]] through [[WALL_SPR_DATA_6]] are the seven frames
of the right-edge wall tile painted every frame by
[[REFRESH_RIGHT_WALL]].  The matching pointer table is
[[WALL_SPR_LO]] / [[WALL_SPR_HI]] (indexed by [[ZP_SPRITE_XREF]]).
Format is identical to [[WALL_L_SPR_DATA]]: 140 bytes, 4 columns
$\times$ 35 rows, column-major, painted via [[INTERLACE_BLIT_P1]] /
[[INTERLACE_BLIT_P2]] into the same three perspective bands.  The
image mirrors the left-wall handle onto the right side of the tile so
both edges of the playfield frame the same shading motif.

