\section{PLAYER\_SPR\_IDLE and \_ACTIVE frames ([[$854C]]--[[$8ABF]])}

The player-body sprite art occupies [[$854C]]--[[$8ABF]], 1396 bytes
total, split between the idle-path and action-path pointer tables.
Each frame is a $3\times$H column-major bitmap (four bytes per row,
since [[DRAW_SPRITE]] runs W+1 inner iterations for [[ZP_SPRITE_W]]
= [[$03]]) and every frame begins with a leading row of zero bytes
when the alignment requires it; [[DRAW_SPRITE]] reads from a fixed
source pointer and walks down the rows so the bitmap's apparent
vertical position inside the frame is chosen to match the
[[ZP_PLAYER_COL]] row fed via [[SMC_SR_YSRC]].

\paragraph{Idle body frames ([[$854C]]--[[$87F7]]).}
[[PLAYER_SPR_IDLE_DATA_0]]--[[PLAYER_SPR_IDLE_DATA_8]] are nine
unique frames, each $\$4\mathrm{C}$ bytes (19~rows $\times$ 4 bytes)
and selected by [[PLAYER_SPR_IDLE_LO]]/[[PLAYER_SPR_IDLE_HI]] indexed
by [[ZP_PLAYER_STANCE]] ([[$03]]..[[$09]]).  The pointer table has
ten entries but entries [[$01]] and [[$03]] both reference
[[PLAYER_SPR_IDLE_DATA_1]], so a stance change between 4 and 6 shows
the same silhouette.  [[DRAW_PLAYER]] uses this set when
[[ZP_ACTION_DIR]] is zero --- player is standing on a floor.

\paragraph{Active body frames ([[$87F8]]--[[$8ABF]]).}
[[PLAYER_SPR_ACTIVE_DATA_0]]--[[PLAYER_SPR_ACTIVE_DATA_8]] are nine
unique frames, of which frames 0--1 are $\$4\mathrm{C}$ bytes
(19~rows) and frames 2--8 are $\$50$ bytes (20~rows).
[[PLAYER_SPR_ACTIVE_LO]]/[[HI]] has ten pointer entries; entry [[$01]]
aliases back to [[PLAYER_SPR_IDLE_DATA_8]], so the same bitmap serves
as both the final idle stance and the first ascent/descent stance.
The stance 3 ([[PLAYER_SPR_ACTIVE_DATA_2]]) and stance 9
([[PLAYER_SPR_ACTIVE_DATA_8]]) frames bracket the full-screen
vertical-motion cycle, drawn by [[DRAW_PLAYER]] after the random
flicker layer whenever [[ZP_ACTION_DIR]] is non-zero.

