\section{HIT\_SPR\_POS frames ([[$8AC0]]--[[$8BD7]])}

[[HIT_SPR_POS_DATA_0]]--[[HIT_SPR_POS_DATA_6]] are the seven
positive-parallax frames of the impact sprite drawn by
[[REFRESH_HIT_ENTITIES]] at the moment a projectile or enemy
collides with an object on the player's right.  Each frame is
$\$28$ bytes (5~rows $\times$ 8 bytes), selected by
[[HIT_SPR_POS_LO]]/[[HIT_SPR_POS_HI]] indexed by the hit-animation
counter.  The negative-parallax mirror lives in
[[HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_0]]--[[HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_6]] at [[$7AD4]]--[[$7BEB]].

\section{PLAYER\_GRID\_SPR\_A tail ([[$8BD8]]--[[$8BFF]])}

