\subsection{Pages 13--18: attract-mode animations and enemy/beam code
([[$1300]]--[[$18FF]])}

The [[$1300]]--[[$18FF]] swappable window is byte-identical to the
[[drol.bin]] copy (the $1300$-page region is part of the persistent
code that is also carried by every level's tracks~5--9 / 10--14 /
etc.\ image and verified to match).  The [[drol]] target decomposes
this range into 14 labelled routines (the beam subsystem tail,
[[BEAM_UPDATE]], [[GAME_START_INIT]], the three enemy-slot
advance/draw pairs, the four attract-mode animations, and the head
of [[FLOOR_BASE_ROW]]); the [[level1]] target mirrors the same
decomposition with [[L1_]]-prefixed labels so the byte-exact output
builds without colliding with the authoritative [[drol]] symbols
[[BEAM_UPDATE]], [[GAME_START_INIT]], [[ENEMY_A_ADVANCE]],
[[ENEMY_A_DRAW]], [[ENEMY_B_ADVANCE]], [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]],
[[ENEMY_C_ADVANCE]], [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]], [[ATTRACT_ANIM_1]]..%
[[ATTRACT_ANIM_4]], [[FLOOR_BASE_ROW_PAD]] and [[FLOOR_BASE_ROW]].

