\subsection{Pages 75--7A: sprite pointer tables and playfield-chrome
sprite pixel data ([[$7500]]--[[$7AFF]])}

The [[$7500]]--[[$7AFF]] swappable window is byte-identical to the
[[drol.bin]] copy that the loader has already deposited at the same
runtime addresses (verified in the earlier invariant: the level-swap
pages match [[drol.bin]] for every byte in this range).  The
[[level1]] target mirrors the [[drol.bin]] decomposition with
[[L1_]]-prefixed labels so the byte-exact output builds without
colliding with the authoritative [[drol]] symbols
[[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_LO]], [[PILLAR_SPR_DATA_0]], and the others.

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{lllll} \toprule
[[L1_]]-label & [[drol]] twin & Span & Bytes & Role \\ \midrule
[[L1_SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_LO]] & [[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_LO]] & [[$7500]]--[[$75FF]] & 256 & 37 sub-tables + null pad \\
[[L1_SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_HI]] & [[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_HI]] & [[$7600]]--[[$76FF]] & 256 & HI-half of the same 37 sub-tables \\
[[L1_PILLAR_SPR_DATA_0]]..[[L1_PILLAR_SPR_DATA_6]] & [[PILLAR_SPR_DATA_0]]..[[PILLAR_SPR_DATA_6]] & [[$7700]]--[[$7AD3]] & 7$\times$140 & 7 pillar frames, 4 cols $\times$ 35 rows \\
[[L1_HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_0]] & [[HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_0]] & [[$7AD4]]--[[$7AFB]] & 40 & frame 0 of the [[HIT_SPR_NEG]] 7-frame set \\
[[L1_HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_1_HEAD]] & first 4 bytes of [[HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_1]] & [[$7AFC]]--[[$7AFF]] & 4 & partial: [[$7500]]--[[$7AFF]] cuts the 40-byte frame \\ \bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The [[L1_HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_1_HEAD]] entry is the only artifact of the
swappable-page boundary: [[HIT_SPR_NEG_DATA_1]]'s full 40~bytes span
[[$7AFC]]--[[$7B23]], so the last 36 bytes sit inside the persistent
[[drol.bin]] region ([[$7B00]]--[[$8BFF]]) loaded from tracks~3--4.
At runtime the two halves are contiguous, but [[level1.bin]] (the
on-disk level-swap image) only carries the first 4 bytes.

