Shape columns express dimensions as ``W,H'' where W is the
[[DRAW_SPRITE]] width operand (actual bytes per row is W+1; see the
``DRAW\_SPRITE W+1 bytes/row'' memory note) and H is the row count,
so the byte total is $(W+1)\times H$.

The [[ENEMY_C_TAIL]] pointer table ships with 9 entries
([[$8C10]] through [[$8C79]]), but [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]]'s steady-mode
path indexes it with [[X]]~=~[[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]] which only takes
values~[[$00]]..[[$06]].  Frames~7 and~8 are therefore never
reached at runtime; frame~7 is half the normal size (7 bytes,
likely a W=1 rather than W=2 silhouette), and frame~8 is a
14-byte all-zero block ending at [[$8C86]].  They are preserved
as labelled residue instead of being folded into raw-HEX padding,
because the pointer table's high-byte side
([[ENEMY_C_TAIL_HI]]) lists their page bytes explicitly, so the
pointers are live data even if no draw path consumes them.

\subsection{Page 8C tail through $B4B0$: sprite pixel data region
([[$8CF5]]--[[$B4B0]])}

The next 10172 bytes ([[$8CF5]]--[[$B4B0]]) hold the bulk of the
level-1 swappable sprite pixel data and pointer tables.  All sub-regions
are indexed from pointer tables either in [[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_LO]]
/ [[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_HI]] (for the players/floor-enemies/rescue
children/entity-grid/companion families) or from the level-swap tail
pointer tables at [[$AFD3]]--[[$B0FF]] (for the projectile/special-puff/
enemy-C/scroll-edge/digit/SPRITE\_TABLE pointer families, which are
[[EQU]]-declared and stored as the [[SPRITE_POINTER_TABLES_TAIL]] raw
byte block within the collection chunk).

