[[BRODERBUND_LOGO_SPR_DATA]] & [[$BCF1]]--[[$BD88]] & 152  & W=18,H=8 (19x8)   & [[ATTRACT_ANIM_4]] tail \\
[[LEVEL1_TAIL_RESIDUE_HEAD]]     & [[$BD89]]--[[$BD8C]] & 4    & ---               & unreferenced \\
[[LEVEL1_TAIL_RESIDUE_FINALISE]] & [[$BD8D]]--[[$BD9F]] & 19   & ---               & unreferenced \\ \bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The enemy-A and enemy-B sprite tables are indexed by
[[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]] through the [[SPRITE_TABLE_A_BODY_LO]] /
[[SPRITE_TABLE_B_LO]] (etc.) pointer tables in the low [[$B0]]
region; those pointers resolve to the frame-0 addresses listed in
each chunk's header comment.  The drol chapter already declares
[[EXTRA_LIFE_SPR]] and [[BRODERBUND_LOGO_SPR]] as cross-target
[[EQU]]s whose values match these data chunks' ORG addresses.

\subsection{Tail residue ([[$BD89]]--[[$BD9F]]): dead RWTS-finalise fragment}

The 23 bytes between [[BRODERBUND_LOGO_SPR_DATA]]'s end and
[[GAME_OVER]] are not sprite padding --- they disassemble as live
6502 code that is a near twin of the [[.finalise]] + restart-skip
bridge inside [[STAGE_RESIDUE_DEAD]] at [[$5E8D]].  Both fragments:

\begin{itemize}
\item load [[ZP_DEAD_SECHDR]] ([[$48]]) indirectly to pull
  [[hdr[4]]] out of a sector header,
\item call into [[NIBBLE_READER_OVL]] ([[$BE5A]], a mid-instruction
  entry into the live [[NIBBLE_READER]] in [[rwts.bin]]),
\item consume the preserved processor flags with [[PLP]] and
  conditionally branch on [[ZP_DEAD_FLAGS]] ([[$47]]).
\end{itemize}

The [[STAGE_RESIDUE_DEAD]] copy's [[PLP]]/[[BNE]]/[[BPL]] triple
branches to a [[.restart_skip]] label at [[$5EAB]] --- a [[BIT]]-abs
mid-entry into a [[GAME_START_INIT]] clone.  The residue at
[[LEVEL1_TAIL_RESIDUE_HEAD]] uses the same pattern but targets
[[$BDAB]], which in the pre-release layout presumably held another
[[GAME_START_INIT]] clone.  In the shipped level-1 image [[$BDAB]]
now lands at the third [[STA ZP_SCORE_1]] inside [[GAME_OVER]],
which is a nonsensical target reached by no live code path.

The decomposition splits the span into two labels:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[LEVEL1_TAIL_RESIDUE_HEAD]] ([[$BD89]]--[[$BD8C]], 4 bytes):
  an orphan [[TSX]] / [[DEY]] / [[BNE $BD87]] prologue whose
  branch target lies inside [[BRODERBUND_LOGO_SPR_DATA]], so the
  fall-through path is the only coherent one.  Almost certainly
  leftover from a pre-release layout where the logo sprite lived
  elsewhere.
\item [[LEVEL1_TAIL_RESIDUE_FINALISE]] ([[$BD8D]]--[[$BD9F]], 19
  bytes): the [[LDX TXT_RETRY_05F8]] / nibble-reader call + flags
  check that maps directly onto the live [[.finalise]] section of
  [[STAGE_RESIDUE_DEAD]].  The final [[LDY #$12]] has no
  instruction after it before [[GAME_OVER]] begins, so whatever
  consumed this [[Y]] value lived in the same pre-release layout.
\end{itemize}

Both chunks are preserved byte-for-byte.  No shipped target
([[boot1]], [[loader]], [[rwts]], [[drol]], or [[level1]]) names
an address inside this range.

