\section{Assembly}

Because the [[level1]] target compiles in isolation (it does not inline
the [[drol]] or [[rwts]] sources), any cross-target symbol
used inside a level-1 code chunk must be declared here with an
[[EQU]].  [[<<level1 defines>>]] is the shared declaration block; keep
it in sync with the authoritative definitions in the
[[drol]]/[[rwts]] chapters.

<<level1 defines>>=

; =========================================================================
;  Cross-target symbol aliases.
;  These EQUs redeclare labels whose bodies live in drol.asm / rwts.asm
;  so the level1 target can reference them by name without pulling the
;  full code chunks.  Keep in sync with the defining chunks.
; =========================================================================

; --- Zero page (shared with drol.asm defines) ---
ZP_HGR_SRC      = $29           ; Hi-res copy source pointer (2 bytes)
ZP_HGR_DST      = $2F           ; Hi-res copy destination pointer (2 bytes)
ZP_SCORE_0      = $2B           ; Score HUD digit 0
ZP_SCORE_1      = $2C           ; Score HUD digit 1
ZP_SCORE_2      = $2D           ; Score HUD digit 2
ZP_CLEAR_COL    = $2E           ; Playfield-clear column counter / right edge
ZP_GAME_OVER    = $39           ; Per-hit credit counter ($FF = game over)
ZP_RESTART_FLAG = $44           ; Cold-start/joystick dual-role dispatch flag
ZP_PLAYER_Y     = $4A           ; Player world Y (floor anchor index)

; --- Code in drol.asm ---
SCREEN_ROW_COPY  = $0100        ; Page-to-page row-wipe routine
ROW_COPY_CLICK   = $01B7        ; Title-wipe per-row speaker-click sfx
INIT_LEVEL_STATE = $11B8        ; Restore ZP from master buffers
GAME_RESTART     = $13C2        ; Lives/score/flag reset sub-entry
PLAYER_MOVE_TICK = $64CB        ; Player-movement-tick dispatcher
MAIN_LOOP        = $67CB        ; Main per-frame loop
LIFE_LOST_RESUME = $720E        ; LIFE_LOST_HANDLER sub-entry (post-transition)
SCREEN_ROW_ADDR_HI  = $72C0     ; Row-base hi bytes (page 1)
SCREEN_ROW_ADDR_LO  = $7380     ; Row-base lo bytes (shared)
SCREEN_ROW_ADDR_HI2 = $7440     ; Row-base hi bytes (page 2)

; --- Code in rwts.asm ---
RWTS_RELOAD     = $BE00         ; Reload loader and fetch next level

; --- HUD column bounds (in drol.asm, bodies inside GAME_START_INIT) ---
HUD_SCORE_COL   = $65AB         ; Left-bound column (playfield start)
HUD_LIVES_COL   = $65A7         ; Right-bound column (playfield end)

; --- Apple II ROM ---
MON_WAIT        = $FCA8         ; Monitor WAIT (delay loop, A = duration)

@

<<level1 prologue>>=

        ORG $0000
        DS $0200,0             ; Pages ZP_PAGE_FLAG-$01 (ZP + stack) not loaded
